title: santa fe corn & cheese squares
directions: Heat oven to 400.
Grease 13X9 pan.

title: fruit punch
directions: Take out
cups
water and bring to boil.
Add Jell-O and sugar.
Stir
until dissolved.
Add all juices and remainder of water.
Add ice and ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
together
eggs, corn syrup, margarine, vanilla and salt. Stir
in
pecans and turn into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for
15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Combine ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Turn into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Crumbled bacon bits may be sprinkled on top before baking for added flavor.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Mix 2 teaspoons mixture with 1 cup boiling water.
Keep remaining tea mixture in tightly sealed container.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix flour, baking powder and sugar. Stir in the milk until blended.
Put batter in baking dish on melted oleo.
Add the fruit on top and pour the water over all. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mom's salmon party ball
directions: Drain salmon and remove any skin or bones.
Combine all but pecans and parsley, mixing well.
Mix pecans and parsley on wax paper.
Form salmon mixture into a ball and roll in pecans/parsley.
Chill several hours before serving with crackers.

title: strawberry gel
directions: Bring to a rolling boil.
Chill until 1/2 set, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Pour over fruit.
Set overnight.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pistachio sour cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat
for
minutes.
Pour
into a well greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from pan after 10
minutes.
Glaze
or
sprinkle with
powdered sugar.

title: split pea and barley soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a 3 to 4-quart pot.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 1 hour.
When peas begin to fall apart and vegetables are tender, soup is done.

title: caramel dip
directions: Use wire whisk to blend.
Great for dipping apple slices.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Line bottom of large pan with 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Mix cheese, Dream Whip, milk and sugar.
Whip until thick.
Spread 1/2 of mixture over cracker crumbs.
Then spread cherries.
Spread rest of mixture and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Chill until ready to serve.
Will keep at least a week.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Thaw the spinach before you do anything else. Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan in oven.
Remove pan.

title: creole casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spread about 1/2 of the Minute rice right from the box in an even layer on bottom.
Cover with 1 cup of grated cheese.
Add remaining rice.
Combine tomatoes and juice, salt and onion in saucepan, crushing tomatoes and mixing well. Bring to a boil.
Pour over layers of rice and cheese.
Bake, covered, in a moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven, uncover and spoon remaining cheese onto rice mixture around edge, leaving center uncovered.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: twenty-four hour slaw
directions: Layer the cabbage, green pepper, onion and pimento in a large container.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix hamburger with onions, egg, Worcestershire and bread or cracker crumbs.
Stuff peppers.
Set on rack in pressure cooker. Mix 1 can tomato soup with 3 tablespoons ketchup and pour over peppers.
Cook 15 minutes in pressure cooker.

title: banana split cake
directions: Place graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan until covered.
Mix pudding according to package instructions and place over top of graham crackers.
Layer bananas on top of pudding, then pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken divan
directions: Beginning with broccoli, layer with sliced chicken and mixture of soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish (2 layers of each).
Cover with cracker crumbs. Drizzle 1/4 cup butter over top. Bake, covered for 30 minutes in 350°.
Uncover last 5 minutes to brown top.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve hard-cooked eggs lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash yolks and mix with ingredients.
Refill egg whites.
Sprinkle with black or red pepper.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Fry the onion and celery in margarine for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add mushroom soup, 1 can of hot water, Cheez Whiz, broccoli and rice. Pour in casserole dish and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: holiday bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from corn and beans, mix together and pour in greased casserole dish.
Mix together soup, sour cream, cheese, onions, salt and pepper.
Spread over bean mixture.
Mix together crushed crackers, almonds, and melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes uncovered.

title: yum yum chixolli
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise and a little curry powder.
Pour over cubed chicken that is already on bottom of Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 15 more minutes or until chicken is done.

title: salmon romanoff
directions: Flake salmon.
Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Combine prepared noodles with salmon, mushrooms, cottage cheese, green onion and dill.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix at medium speed until blended.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken taco rice
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Cut peppers into strips.
Cook and stir chicken in hot oil until lightly browned.
Add broth, tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add corn and peppers.
Bring to a full boil. Stir in rice.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix cheese, sour cream and salad dressing mix. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate for several hours. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: corn souffle
directions: Stir together.
Use a large bowl for oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sticky bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Wait 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup melted lukewarm oleo and lukewarm milk.
Add a pinch of salt and sugar or honey; keep mixture lukewarm at all times.
Add flour until mixture is stiff.
Knead for about 15 minutes.
Let rise in warm place, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in water until tender; drain. In a small sauce pan, saute onions in margarine over low heat until they are clear. Cook rice; add broccoli, onions, Cheez Whiz and rice to broccoli. Add soup and mix well. Pour into casserole dish. Top with shredded cheese; cover and bake at 350° until bubbly. Serve and enjoy!

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cook 10 to 15 minutes. Pack in jars and cold pack 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bring soup and margarine to boil.
Add corn.
Mix with cooked rice.
Pour in baking dish and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in Dutch oven size pan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and melt in Hershey candy, Nestle chips and marshmallows.
Pour in greased pan; cool and cut.

title: corn-torte
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Remove cover during last 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple-strawberry cobbler
directions: Mix apples, strawberries, sugar and cinnamon. Pour into dish. Mix remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls on fruit mixture. Bake for 15 minutes at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir in nuts, etc.
Bake 50 minutes or until done.

title: 5 pound fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and cream for 13 minutes.
Add vanilla, chips and marshmallow cream.
Mix well and pour in greased baking dish.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix everything together and pour into lightly greased pan. Use the pan or loaf pans of your choice.
Cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: In a large saucepan, heat milk and water nearly to boiling. Add grits, cooking and stirring, until very thick; add salt, butter and garlic cheese.
In a small bowl, beat eggs lightly; spoon a little of the hot grits into the egg mixture, then combine with rest of grits.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: elegant chicken breasts
directions: Line a greased pan with the chipped beef.
Wrap a strip of bacon around each chicken breast and arrange in casserole. Combine remaining ingredients and spread over the chicken.
Bake for 1 hour, covered, at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 10 to 15 minutes.
May be sprinkled with a little paprika, if desired. Serve on wild rice.
Very good.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and taco mix.
Spread in a 12 x 7-inch pan. Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.
(This can also be heated and served with warm tortillas, delicious!)

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off each pepper.
Remove seeds and white membrane. In a small bowl combine beef, onion, pimiento, salt and pepper. Spoon into peppers.
Stand peppers up in crock-pot.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mustard to soup.
Pour over peppers. Cover pot; cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: cranberry christmas punch
directions: Mix.
You can also use pineapple-orange concentrate.

title: roasted vegetable salad
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Place the vegetables in a large mixing bowl and toss with the olive oil, salt and pepper to coat evenly.
Spread the vegetables in 1 layer on a large roasting pan and roast in the preheated oven for 45 minutes.
Remove the roasting pan from the oven and allow the vegetables to cool for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil canned sweet potatoes (large size) with lid on for about 10 to 15 minutes to soften.
Beat with an electric mixer, all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Sprinkle on topping and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Put in double boiler and beat 7 minutes or until a hard ball forms when dropped in cold water the white sugar, egg white, cold water and baking powder.
Cut off head and add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cooled cake while frosting is warm.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine butter and onion; saute.
Add flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg gradually.
Stir until smooth.
Add to it the broth and milk.

title: jenny's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the margarine. Add sugars gradually and mix well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Stir in soda, salt, flour and oats.
Form dough into small balls. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Good for Christmas or Valentine.
Makes almost 2 gallons, 30 servings.

title: ham and swiss sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Spread mixture on bottom half of rolls.
Wrap individually in foil and bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Sandwiches may be refrigerated for several days.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion, parsley and garlic in hot fat until soft.
Add tomato sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add ground beef and Italian sausage, browned in olive oil.
Add rest of ingredients. Cook in slow oven 3 or more hours.
This freezes well.
Makes 8 or more servings.

title: when the gang's all here chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in ungreased baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top of chicken.
Dilute soup with water.
Spread over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle the stuffing mix on top.
Put several pats of butter on top of stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: western style beef skillet
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add beef; cook until no longer pink.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to combine.
Cover; reduce heat to medium.
Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: super spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and drain excess grease.
Mix tomato soup, tomato sauce, ground beef and chili powder in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 7 hours.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Crush 1 large bag of Doritos and put half in bottom of large dish.
Add all other ingredients.
Top with remainder of Doritos. Put Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until real bubbly, about 25 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; add stuffing mix.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add 1/2 stuffing mixture to squash mixture and mix well.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake in casserole dish at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in taco seasoning.
Add tomatoes, corn and pinto beans.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cornbread mix.
Bake at 425° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: crab souffle
directions: In a bowl, lightly mix the bread, celery and onion.
Put this mixture into a greased 4-qt. casserole dish.
Mix together the crab meat, mayonnaise, pimiento, salt and dry mustard, and pour over the bread mixture.
Beat the eggs well, then add the milk.
Pour this over the other ingredients and top with the shredded Swiss cheese. Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until puffed and lightly browned on top.

title: carrot cake(three 9-inch layer pans)
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and sugar and pour over chopped nuts.
Add to mixture of eggs, salad oil and carrots. Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs, Karo syrup, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: st.  patrick's punch
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Use blender or electric mixer.
Serve immediately.
Double amount for larger quantities.
Very refreshing and a pretty pale green color.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese in bowl.
Add drained pineapple and oranges.
Add room temperature cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: chocolate gook
directions: Melt stick of butter; add flour and nuts.
Mix together with spoon and pat in bottom of oblong greased pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and add the milk and melted margarine.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach-orange salad
directions: Stir and chill. Drizzle over salad just before serving.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into a large mold or in individual molds.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Garnish with sweet pickle pieces and stuffed olives.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as usual.
Cut pepperoni in small pieces.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add the diced peppers, onion and mushrooms to the hamburger; mix together.
Place the mixed macaroni and hamburger mixture into greased casserole.
Top with the shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° until hot and the cheese is golden brown.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Mix butter and graham cracker crumbs together for base. Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Layer the rest in order given. Bake at 325 for 30 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add salt and sugar. Blend in flour. Knead dough until smooth. Cut into small pieces. Roll into ropes and twist into desired shapes. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Brush pretzels with beaten egg. Sprinkle with coarse salt. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt and pepper; let cool. Toss together lettuce, tomatoes, onion, cheese and dressing. Add beef to lettuce mixture. Crush nachos and add part to mixture. Put remaining nachos on top.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, almonds and sunflower seeds.
Crumble Ramen noodles and mix with cabbage mixture.
Mix flavor packet from noodles with oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over slaw and mix.

title: krazy korn
directions: Mix corn and nuts in large bowl.
Combine sugar, butter and syrup in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in vanilla. Pour over corn mixture.
Spread out on wax paper.

title: lo-cal smoked casserole
directions: In a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, put about 6 slices of bread on bottom of dish.
Put all of the smoked chicken or turkey over the bread.
Add layer of ham. Cook broccoli until tender, then layer it on the ham. Add layer of onion and Swiss cheese.
Add cream of mushroom soup. Salt and pepper.
Put in microwave for 20 minutes.

title: fruit cake(very good)
directions: Mix
eggs, sugar, butter, flour and baking powder.
Add the rest of the ingredients and bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 275°.

title: grilled swordfish with fresh tomato-herb salsa
directions: Bring medium saucepan of water to boil.
Add tomatoes and blanch 30 seconds.
Drain; transfer to medium bowl.
Cover with cold water; cool.
Peel tomatoes; cut in half.
Squeeze out juices.
Chop tomatoes; transfer to bowl.
Add herbs, shallot, vinegar and 1 tablespoon oil.
Season with salt and pepper. Prepare barbecue or preheat broiler.
Brush fish with oil. Sprinkle with generous amount of peppercorns and salt.
Grill until just cooked through, about 4 minutes per side.
Transfer to plates.
Spoon salsa over and serve.

title: chinese tuna dinner
directions: Blend all ingredients together, saving a few noodles to sprinkle on top.
Bake casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy egg custard
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Gradually stir in scalded milk.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 40 minutes or until knife inserted between center and edges comes out clean.
Cook on rack and chill.

title: garden style barbecue beans
directions: Combine onion and green peppers in a 1-quart microwavable casserole.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes until crisp and tender.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Cover; microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes, or until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: mint cheesecake brownie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs.
Spread into well greased 13 x 9 inch pan; bake 15 minutes.
In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs, extract and food coloring; mix well.
Pour evenly over brownie.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Spread with frosting. Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Pour ingredients into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Bring sugar and pineapple to a boil.
Dissolve gelatine in water and lemon juice and add to pineapple mixture.
Let it get stone cold.
Slice cake in 1/4-inch slices.
Line pan.
Mix whipped cream with cooled pineapple mixture.
Pour 1/2 over cake. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries.
Put 1 more layer of cake, mixture, nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: french onion soup
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Brown onion in oil over medium heat. Heat soup mix and water.
Pour into 4 individual casseroles. Arrange browned onions, followed by a layer of French bread over soup.
Sprinkle with the three cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Bake 15 minutes or until bubbly and hot.
Serve immediately.

title: layered salad
directions: Prepare peas according to package directions; cool.
Layer vegetables in large glass bowl in the order given, starting with the lettuce and ending with the peas.
Mix together the sour cream and mayonnaise; spread over peas, covering completely.
Chill for at least 3 hours or overnight.
Before serving, top with grated cheese and bacon.
This recipe serves plenty as a side dish.

title: caramel pound cake
directions: Grease just bottom of pan.
Cook at 300° for 2 hours or until done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage; brown and drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer bread, sausage, cheese, another layer of bread, sausage and cheese.
Add milk to beaten eggs.
Salt and pepper.
Pour over casserole; put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable cheese salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Chop onion.
Heat vinegar and sugar just until sugar melts.
Stir in Miracle Whip and pour over vegetables.
Mix in grated cheese.

title: chocolate tease
directions: In a blender, put eggs, chocolate, rum and coffee and mix at high speed until well mixed.
Add milk and blend another 2 minutes.
Pour into dessert cups and chill 4 hours or overnight. Top with whipped topping and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crawfish stuffed peppers
directions: Cut top off peppers and clean.
Parboil 10 minutes.
Saute crawfish, onions and celery in oil.
If you have fat, add to oil. Saute mixture until vegetables are tender.
Add crabmeat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add bread crumbs.
Stuff peppers. Add water to baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken aloha
directions: In a saucepan, cook celery and green pepper in hot oil until tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, pie filling, water and soy sauce. Add chicken.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until hot.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.
Sprinkle almonds over each serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a saucepan, boil sliced squash in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Add butter and mash.
Combine sugar, egg, mayonnaise and 1/2 cup cheese.
Stir into squash.
Pour into a 9-inch greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and pecans over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned and cheese is melted.

title: banana split muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, and salt in large bowl.
Beat egg in small bowl; stir in dressing.
Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Stir in bananas.

title: spinach manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Cook ground beef for 5 minutes; drain.
In large bowl combine beef, Ricotta cheese, spinach, oregano, salt, pepper and scallions.
Fill each manicotti with 2 tablespoons meat mixture and place in baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over manicotti.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: picante sauce
directions: Put peeled and diced tomatoes and diced onions and peppers in a large pot.
Add all other ingredients and cook 2 to 3 hours. Place in hot jars and seal.
Let sit until cool.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Chop very fine both kinds of peppers, then combine with sugar and vinegar.
Bring to rolling boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute; remove from fire.
Add Certo; mix well.
Pour into hot jars; seal with paraffin wax.

title: shrimp and cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on English muffins and put in freezer.
Cut in wedges.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in fruit.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into an 8-inch Pyrex dish; refrigerate until firm.
Store remaining gelatin mixture at room temperature. Spread congealed gelatin with sour cream.
Spoon remaining gelatin over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.
Pecans may be added when fruit is added.

title: strawberry party cake
directions: Mix and bake about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: jello pie(sugar-free)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Combine cream cheese, sweetened (or sugar) and vanilla.
Add jello; mix well.
Fold whipped milk into this and pour into a graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: mom's pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and lard into crumbs.
Beat egg; add vinegar and water.
Pour into flour mixture and mix until it forms a ball.
Can be frozen.

title: lemon pie
directions: Place in cooked pie shell or graham cracker crust. Refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add milk and cream cheese.
Stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Stir in meat, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and parsley; heat.
Serve hot.

title: prairieland pot roast
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper; brown in 1/4 cup dressing in Dutch oven over low heat.
Add remaining dressing and water. Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add onions, carrots and potatoes. Cover and continue to cook 1 hour longer or until meat and potatoes are tender.
Remove from pot meat and vegetables.
Add flour to water, then pour into hot liquid in pan.
Cook, stirring constantly until boils.
Simmer about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve with meat and vegetables.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain juice from peaches into measuring cup.
Spread sliced peaches in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle jello over peaches and dry cake mix over jello.
Slice margarine over cake mix; add water to peach juice if necessary to make 1 1/2 cups.
Pour over top of cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable batter
directions: Combine, in a mixing bowl the flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until broken into fine particles.
Stir in egg and sweet milk.
Mix well.

title: jean's vegetable quiche
directions: Prepare brown rice as directed on package.
Allow to become room temperature.
Mix rice, margarine, 1/4 cup of egg substitute and 1/2 of cheese.
Spray a 9 1/2 x 11-inch dish well with Pam. Press into dish.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon crisp; remove bacon (reserve 2 tablespoons drippings in container). Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute onion in drippings until tender. Add potatoes and water; cover and simmer until tender. Stir in milk, corn, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat. Stir until well heated. Place a serving
in separate individual bowls. Sprinkle crumbled bacon on each serving.

title: mom's bean soup
directions: Sort through beans and remove any foreign material.
Wash beans in strainer, rinsing several times.
Put in 3 qt. saucepan and add 4 c. of water.
Put a lid on pan and let beans soak overnight. Remove any floaters.
Add water as needed until it covers beans by about 1 inch.
Add ingredients.
Gently stir to mix.
Bring to a low boil and simmer with lid on for 2-3 hours, or until beans are soft.

title: spring salad
directions: Drain fruit juice and add lemon juice and water.
Stir in pudding and bring to boil.
Cool and add remaining ingredients. Fold in whipped topping and fold in banana.
Chill overnight.

title: crispy baked chicken with peaches
directions: Place cut-up chicken, slightly salted, skin side up in a baking pan large enough so the pieces don't overlap.
Mix entire bottle of dressing with the peach juice (reserving peach halves for later) and pour over chicken.
Cover (with foil if necessary) and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.
Then add peaches, continue basting, and bake until chicken looks dark, glazed and crisp.
This will take an additional 20 to 30 minutes.
(Particularly good with rice.)

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Spray casserole with Pam.
Layer vegetables, chopped egg, half of mushroom soup and half of the grated cheese and repeat for second layer.
Top with crumbled saltines and dot with butter. Sprinkle parsley and/or chives on top if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate fudge cookies
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa; combine with sugar and beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Add vanilla and eggs and mix well; combine flour, soda, powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk while mixing on low speed, stir in pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter krinkles
directions: In saucepan, bring oleo, syrup and sugar to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Pour over corn flakes.
Drop by spoonful on buttered surface.
These may be frozen for future use. This recipe may be halved.

title: canadian mud pies
directions: Add butter, sugar, milk and cocoa together and bring to a boil for 15 seconds, then add the coconut, vanilla and oatmeal until thick.
Should be really thick!!!
Drop by the spoonful onto wax paper.
Let it dry and enjoy your Canadian treats.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar into shortening.
Blend in peanut butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix soda with flour.
Blend into first mixture.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Shape dough into rolls. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill until firm.
Place roll of chilled dough on cutting board. Cut into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes. Remove cookies to cooling racks.
Store crisp cookies in cookie tin.

title: lemon sandwiches
directions: In top of double boiler, combine eggs, sugar, butter, juice and rind of lemons. Cook, stirring until thick (like mayonnaise). Remove from heat and cool. Add mayonnaise and chopped nuts. Spread thin on bread. Cut sandwiches into 4 triangles for a delightful party sandwich.

title: scallops of chicken in marsala wine
directions: Beat chicken into thin slices.
Coat with flour.
Heat butter and oil. Add chicken and brown on both sides.
Add Marsala wine. Simmer 10 minutes, uncovered, and serve immediately.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Cook and stir beef and onion until brown.
Stir in salt.
Spread beef in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate remaining pie. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pere ripiene(pears stuffed with gorgonzola cheese)
directions: With a	small
sharp knife, peel the pears and cut them in half
lengthwise.
Remove
the
cores
and	scoop
a
scant tablespoon of pulp out of each of the pear halves.	To prevent the fruit
from
turning
brown,
paint
each
section of pear inside and out with a pastry brush, dipped in lemon juice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Spoon small portions onto ungreased cookie sheet. Press flat.
Bake 325° to 350° for 10 minutes.

title: joan's favorite quiche
directions: Mix together the eggs, milk, mayonnaise and flour.
Add the crab or shrimp meat, the grated cheese and onions; mix well.
Pour mixture into an 8 inch unbaked pie shell (pre-made frozen is good), and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: flank steak marinated
directions: Place all ingredients in glass dish or stainless steel container at least 6 hours before baking.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap; bake at 375° until done the way you like your meat.

title: skillet chili
directions: In a large skillet, brown onion and hamburger.
Drain.
Stir in chili seasoning and sugar, then add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use 1/2 of beef in ball.
Roll ball in other 1/2 of beef.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: broccoli 'n cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion and margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly on top.

title: chicken and rice casserole 2
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour into large baking pan (lasagna pan).
Place fryer pieces on top of rice mixture.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven, covered with foil.
Bake 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: make-ahead meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly; shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake about 10 minutes or until done.
Cool meatballs in pan about 5 minutes. Place in freezer for 15 minutes.
Remove and pack tightly in 1-quart freezer container and return to freezer.
Makes 35 meatballs.

title: company casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown beef and stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cheeses, sour cream, onions and green pepper. Spread half of the noodles in a 2 quart greased casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture and then remaining noodles.
Spread beef sauce on top and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6-8.

title: coconut scotch bars
directions: Place margarine and sugar in large pot.
Heat over low setting until bubbly.
Cool a little.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and flour; beat until smooth.
Mix in coconut and pecans.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Fill 2 loaf pans sprayed with vegetable oil and 1/2 of a loaf pan.
Make another batch and fill 2 more loaf pans and finish filling the other 1/2 pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until dry.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: horseradish butter
directions: Cream together the butter, horseradish, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Top with snipped parsley.
Serve with hot, cooked corn-on-the-cob.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: southwest skillet
directions: Cook beef with chili powder in skillet until browned. Pour off fat. Stir in soup, water, tomatoes and beans; heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in rice. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Top with cheese. Serve with tortilla chips. Serves 4.

title: christmas peppermint ice
directions: Melt the vanilla chips.
Add the crushed candy canes and peppermint extract.
Stir well.
Pour onto a 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet, covered with wax paper.
Let chill.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: tortilla snacks
directions: Place flour tortillas on baking sheet.
Spread each with refried beans mixed with salsa. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Top with sour cream and black olives.
Cut in quarters to serve.

title: percolator punch
directions: In a percolator basket combine the brown sugar, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Add the liquid ingredients to the pot and perk as for coffee.

title: chicken curry
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter and remove from skillet. Add remaining butter and let it melt.
Saute onion and celery but do not let it brown. Add curry powder and ginger.
Stir in flour, then the broth. Stir constantly over moderate heat.
Add the wine and the cream. Taste and add salt and pepper if necessary.
Add the chicken and mushrooms to the sauce and heat thoroughly.
Serve with hot, fluffy rice and condiments, such as chutney, chopped peanuts, coconut and sieved eggs.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in bacon drippings.
Combine egg, buttermilk and soda; mix well. Stir into flour mixture, mixing well.
Cut each wiener into 10 pieces.
Dip into batter, covering completely (wooden toothpicks work well for dipping).
Drop into 3 to 4 inches hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Great party snack.

title: angel food cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine egg whites, cream of tartar, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat until foamy, then add small amounts of 3/4 cup sugar, beating after each addition.
Continue to beat until holds peaks.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger
and chopped onion in pan.
Add seasonings to hamburger.	Set
aside.
Cut
and boil potatoes until done, then mash
them.
Mix hamburger and vegetables together in baking pan, 9 x 12-inches.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Heat in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: granny wedding cookies
directions: Mix ingredients with hands, Shape into balls abut the size of acorns.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Let cool about five minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: senator russell sweet potatoes
directions: Mix well all ingredients and pour into a baking dish.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken and pork; debone and skin, then ground up.
Brown beef and onions.
Cook cubed potatoes and drain.

title: supper medley(a delicious skillet dinner)
directions: Melt the shortening in a large skillet (which has a tight fitting cover).
Add the meat and brown it.
Add the chopped onions and green pepper and mix the meat.
Add the mushrooms. Arrange the dry noodles over the top of the meat and vegetables. Sprinkle the grated cheese over all and add the tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover.
Place over high flame.
When steaming, turn to simmer flame and cook for 1 hour.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Heat tomatoes on top of stove.
Add cream and crackers to thicken.
Add sugar and salt and pepper.
Heat and mix well.

title: yummers
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into little balls. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chilled coffee(low calorie)
directions: Blend all ingredients except ice in blender.
Add one ice cube at a time.
Blend until smooth.
Serves 1.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Marinate roast in plastic bag with remaining ingredients overnight in refrigerator.
Save marinade and place roast, fat side up, in shallow roasting pan.
Season with salt and pepper. Insert meat thermometer and roast until desired results.
Baste several times during roasting.
Remove roast from oven and carve thinly across the grain.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken, onion, cream of mushroom soup, strips of flour tortillas, bell pepper and cheese.
Start over with chicken, onion, cream of chicken soup, flour tortilla strips, bell pepper and cheese.
Top with Rotel then 1/2 c. chicken broth.
Bake covered 30 minutes, then uncover for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mrs. bennett's best clam chowder
directions: In a large pot, place potatoes, onions and celery.
Open the cans of clams; drain juice over vegetables.
Vegetables should be just covered.
If more liquid is needed to cover them, add water. Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer until tender.
Add clams; bring to boil.
Add cornstarch to half and half.
Add this mixture to the vegetables; cut back down to a simmer.
Add all other ingredients; stir well.
Serves 4.

title: wild rice and cranberry pilaf
directions: Rinse rice with cold water; drain.
In saucepan, combine rice and chicken broth.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in barley, cranberries (apricots or cherries if preferred) and butter.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until rice and barley are tender and liquid is absorbed, stirring once.
Fluff rice with fork; stir in almonds.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Dissolve together lemon Jell-O, salt and boiling water.
Add cold water and vinegar to dissolved mixture.
Stir together and fold into Jell-O mixture the mayonnaise, sour cream, dry mustard, onion, cabbage, carrot, bell pepper, pimento and parsley.
Pour into mold.
Chill until thick (approximately 3 hours).

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, form cakes and fry in butter.

title: box pumpkin cake
directions: Put pumpkin in a large bowl; add eggs and beat well.
Add cake mix and soda and beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost or serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken bake
directions: Melt oleo and mix with stuffing.
Put 1/2 of stuffing mix in baking dish.
Pour half of broth over stuffing.
Add chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Add remainder of stuffing and pour the rest of the broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This dish can be made ahead of time and be refrigerated.

title: charles' favorite potato peelings
directions: Heavy peel (not thin) your potatoes and cover completely in hot water and soak for 10 minutes.
Wash 3 times; if peelings are still very dark, scrape off with a sharp knife.
Cut peelings into 3 to 4-inch pieces and mix in large bowl with meal, salt and pepper.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Blend pulp
and
eggs.	Add
milk
and dry ingredients. Stir in margarine.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: quick mix biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking sheet.
Combine quick mix and liquid in medium bowl.
Stir until just blended.
Drop dough by tablespoons onto greased sheet pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes.
Dissolve jello; add sugar in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add potatoes; cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine Bisquick, milk, egg and sugar.
Stir until blended. Do not overbeat.
Fold in berries.
Fill greased muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding, milk and sugar in medium saucepan and stir over medium heat until pudding starts to boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and stir until creamy.
Pour into pie crust and let cool.
May be topped with Cool Whip before serving.
If preferred, chocolate pudding can be substituted for vanilla pudding.
It's even better.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Knead until dough is firm.
Pinch off size of golf ball and roll out; put into baking pan.
Makes 24 biscuits.
Cook at 500° until light brown.

title: peppermint twist punch
directions: Combine orange juice, limeade and lemonade concentrate.
Add tray of ice cubes and pineapple juice.
Mix juices thoroughly and chill.
Just before serving, add ice cream using mixer to blend. Stir in strawberries and add ginger ale.
Stir.
Serve.
Add vodka if desired.

title: orange marmalade cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful and bake in fairly hot oven.

title: bubble buns
directions: Lightly grease tube pan.
Place rolls in.
Sprinkle with pudding.
Melt butter.
Add sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour over rolls.
Cover tight with foil.
Leave on counter overnight. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes (or more until lightly browned).
Let stand 5 minutes. Invert on plate.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello.
Let cool slightly.
Add bananas, nuts, pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Pour into dish.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in a buttered casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Put in pan and bring to a boil:
2 sticks oleo, water and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt and soda. Pour hot mixture over this.
Add eggs, 1/2 cup buttermilk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well and bake at 350° on large greased cookie sheet about 20 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Place steak in crock-pot.
Mix tomatoes and soup together. Pour over steak.
Cook on low for 10 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and lemon peel to creamed mixture.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Add alternately with milk.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Brush on Glaze.

title: easy fudge frosting
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the sugar, cream and salt; beat until smooth.
Place over low flame and cook and stir only until mixture bubbles up well around edges. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and remaining sugar and beat until smooth.
(If necessary, place over bowl of cold water until thick enough to spread.)

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Scatter nuts in bottom of pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Mix pudding, sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top. Follow with melted butter.
Let set overnight or let rise several hours at room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Dump immediately onto serving plate.

title: nicole's holiday cheese balls
directions: Dice onion and set aside.
Chop beef squares into small pieces (dime size).
Mix about a handful of the chopped beef, onion, Hidden Valley Ranch and cream cheese together.
Mix until all is well blended.
Make into balls.
Roll balls around on a plate with the leftover chip chop beef and coat the entire outside of balls. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: sunday morning rolls
directions: Mix the flour and sugar.
Add milk, mayonnaise and egg.
Beat for 1 minute.
Grease muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soup and pepper; mix well.
Mix together green beans and 1 1/2 cups French fried onions.
Pour into baking dish. Pour soup mixture over green bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with 1 1/2 cups French fried onions; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: lime-garlic chicken
directions: Combine first four ingredients in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add chicken and turn to coat.
Rub lime mixture under chicken skin.
Cover and refrigerate chicken 1 hour, turning occasionally. Prepare barbecue over medium-high
heat, season chicken generously with salt and pepper.
Grill until chicken is cooked through, turning occasionally, about 12 minutes.
Transfer to platter; garnish with additional cilantro.
Serve with warmed black beans, tortillas and a fresh fruit salad.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir well.
Serve with crackers, Triscuits, etc.
Or, cut out the center of rye loaf; put dip in loaf and serve with pieces of rye loaf.

title: cabbage with cheese and bacon
directions: Place water and salt in a 2-quart casserole; arrange cabbage in spoke-fashion with core at outside edge.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 6 minutes; rotate casserole 1/2 turn.
Microwave until crisp-tender, 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Drain liquid, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Mix reserved liquid, soup, mustard and celery seed. Pour over wedges.
Cover tightly and microwave until hot, 3 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat butter until smooth.
Add sugar and beat well.
Blend in honey.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at medium speed after each addition.
Blend dry ingredients.
Add it alternately with buttermilk.
Toss reserved 1/2 cup flour with raisins and figs.
Fold fruit and nuts into batter.

title: easy etouffee(shrimp or crawfish)
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in oleo.
Add crawfish tails, crawfish fat, salt and pepper.
Cook on high for 20 minutes.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini custard
directions: In saucepan, cook zucchini in small amount of salted water with garlic, about 15 minutes.
Drain; discard garlic.
Place zucchini in buttered shallow casserole.
Beat together with fork the egg, sour cream, seasoned salt, pepper and 1/4 cup Parmesan. Pour mixture over zucchini.
Dot with margarine; sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until set.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: colucci chocolate cake with soft chocolate frosting
directions: Dissolve baking soda and baking powder into sour milk.
Mix all ingredients together and blend until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Stir soda into buttermilk and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in nutmeg, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and milk alternately in 3 or more portions, beginning and ending with the flour.
Divide dough.
On a floured board, roll dough to about 1/8-inch thick, cut with a cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: dijon potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin.
Rinse under cold running water to remove most of the starch.
Dry well.
Melt margarine and saute potatoes until golden.
Add water, salt and pepper; cover and cook gently for 20 minutes.
Drain potatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over potatoes just before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Doritos and dressing).
Toss and serve.
Do not mix in Doritos and dressing until ready to use.

title: snapper veracruz
directions: Place fish fillets on a baking pan, skin side down.
Baste fish with margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread 1/3 cup marinated vegetables over the top of each fillet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until the fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls. Roll in flaked coconut.
Makes about 125 cookies.

title: shrimp snack puffs
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Melt shortening in boiling water.
Add dry ingredients, all at once, to boiling liquid, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture leaves sides of pan in smooth compact ball.
Remove from heat; cool about 1 minute. Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each addition until mixture is smooth again.
Add shrimp.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix together all ingredients.
Put into a pretty serving dish and decorate with fruit of some kind.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar with flour and butter; add eggs, buttermilk and coconut.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° to 325° until done.

title: tasty (easy) chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt.
Dip in salad dressing and then in bread crumbs.
Spray Pam on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In large saucepot, saute potatoes and celery in butter or margarine for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium; stir in flour. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes, until potatoes are tender, stirring often.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese until melted.
Add beer or broth or water (whichever you choose), salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Over medium heat, cook 5 minutes more until heated through.
Ready to eat.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place chicken pieces in dish. Add other ingredients on top of chicken. Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in mixture and add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Pour in 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased, floured bread pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bacon wrapped hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Shape mixture into 6 or 7 patties, each about 3/4-inch thick. Crisscross 2 half slices bacon on each patty, tucking ends under.
Place patties on racks in shallow roasting pan.
Cook uncovered at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and Cool Whip together. Roll 1 teaspoon dough into ball; roll in 10x sugar. Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet 10 to 15 minutes or until set.

title: pumpkin chiffon
directions: Mix pudding and milk; add pumpkin, cinnamon and Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread balance of Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: pastitso
directions: You will need 1 deep pan.

title: best ever barbecue beans 'n beef
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and bell pepper in a skillet.
Cook until ground beef is browned, then drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nanny's old-time buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter soft.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add flour and eggs and beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain. Pour in mushroom soup, sour cream and green chilies.
Let simmer a few minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix corn flakes and melted margarine.
Put half in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put shredded cabbage on top of this.
Mix together celery soup, milk, grated cheese and onion.
Pour on top of cabbage.
Sprinkle remaining corn flake mixture on this.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and onion together.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook on low for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Doritos.
Sprinkle over individual servings as served.

title: english pea-egg casserole
directions: Put half of the peas, pimento, cheese and eggs in layers in a casserole. Repeat layers. Cover with mushroom soup and add buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 large servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until the center rises.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy low-fat lemon brownies
directions: Make the angel food cake mix according to directions on box. Mix lemon pie filling in with angel food cake mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil water, add sugar and let simmer.
Add instant coffee. Simmer for one hour.
Cool to room temperature.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Makes 1 quart and 1 fifth.

title: melt in your mouth peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and water.
Cook on a medium/medium-high fire until mixture "balls" in water (it should stick to your teeth) approximately 30 to 35 minutes, stirring continually.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix yeast with the water and let dissolve.
Mix all other ingredients except flour and add yeast mixture. Stir real good and then add flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll out and bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: lime sweet pickles
directions: Soak pickles 24 hours in 2 cups slack lime dissolved in 2 gallons of water; drain and rinse in cold water.
Soak in clear water 3 hours; drain and cover with towel.
Let stand overnight. Heat in large boiling pan until boiling.
Reduce heat.
Jar and seal.
I find it better to start around 2 or 3 o'clock in the afternoon.
This works better for me.
You may find lime at grocery stores, hardware stores, nurseries or seed and feed stores.
Remember the lime must be slack.

title: very good pie crust
directions: Blend flour, lard, sugar and salt, then add well beaten egg, vinegar and cold water.
This makes three 2 crust shells or enough for 5 single crusts.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Bake 55 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
Freezes well up to 2 to 3 months.
Defrost at room temperature 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, vinegar and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1/2 minute.
Add Certo.
Pour in jelly glasses.
Makes 2 pints.

title: liver pate
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or processor.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: In a large pot, cover chicken with water; add celery, halved onion and garlic clove and boil until done.
Reserve chicken stock.
Remove meat from bones.
Cook rice, using 5 cups of stock, until all liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add taco mix, chili powder and salsa.
Spread refried beans onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with meat mixture.
Cover and microwave on High for 8 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and cover for 2 minutes.
Top with dollops of sour cream.
Sprinkle with chives.
Serve as dip with taco chips or spread on soft tortillas and top with onions, tomatoes and olives.

title: chicken enchilada soup
directions: Add 1 Tbsp. of oil to a large soup pot over medium heat. Add chicken breasts to pot and brown for 4 to 5 minutes per side. Set chicken aside. Add onions and garlic to pot and saute over medium heat for about 2 minutes, or until onions begin to become translucent. Add chicken broth. Combine masa harina with 2 cups of water in a medium bowl and whisk until blended. Add masa mixture to pot with onions, garlic and broth. Add remaining water, enchilada sauce, Velveeta cheese and spices to pot and bring mixture to a boil. Shred the chicken into small, bite-size pieces and add it to the pot. Reduce heat and simmer soup for 30 to 40 minutes or until thick. Serve soup in cups or bowls, and garnish with shredded cheddar cheese, crumbled corn tortilla chips, and pico de gallo.

title: refrigerator roll dough
directions: Melt together water and oleo.
Add sugar, salt, yeast and beaten eggs.
Add 4 cups of flour.
Mix well and then add remaining 4 cups flour.
Beat well or mix well with hands.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Use to make Bierocks and Cinnamon Rolls.

title: corn casserole
directions: Add first 3 ingredients together. Pour into casserole dish. Cover with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and arrange in 2-quart baking dish in layered rows. Sprinkle chopped onion, salt and pepper over potatoes.
Pour soup over all and top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Serves 6.

title: energy candy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out and cut into squares or roll into balls.
Refrigerate.
Kids love it and it's easy for them to make themselves, kneading ingredients together with thoroughly washed hands.

title: cheesy reuben appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 c. Swiss cheese, dressing and corned beef. Spread in pie plate.
Top with sauerkraut and remaining swiss cheese.
Can be refrigerated up to 24 hours.
Bake 15-20 minutes at 400 degrees.
Serve hot with pretzel crackers or cocktail bread.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Mix mashed potatoes and any combination of meat, onion, rice or cheese plus salt and pepper.
Add enough milk and melted butter to moisten and shape into balls.
Roll in beaten egg, then crumbs, egg and crumbs again.
Cook in hot fat.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo. Saut onions and bell pepper. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese. Put into casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Add grated cheese on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Frost.

title: holiday jello ring
directions: Mix Jell-O into boiling water until dissolved.
Then add the applesauce.
Pour into your Tupperware Jell-O ring.
Chill until set, approximately 4 to 6 hours.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 3 tablespoons reserved pineapple juice. Add cheese and pineapple chunks and mix well. Put in greased 1-quart casserole. Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 3 or 4-quart casserole dish.
Fry bacon over moderate heat until it is free of its fat and is brown but not crisp.
Drain and set aside on a paper towel.
Add onion to the bacon fat and cook for 8 to 10 minutes until they are transparent but not brown.
Mix in green pepper and cook for another 3 to 4 minutes.
Add in rice and stir the rice until the grains become opaque and milky.
Then add garlic, tomatoes, bacon, thyme, salt and pepper.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour in chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Add ham and stir.
Cover and place on lower third of oven.
Cook for 10 minutes and add the shrimp (push shrimp through the rice).
Cook again until stock is absorbed and rice is tender.
If at any time it appears dry, add a tablespoon of stock to it.
Garnish with parsley.

title: potato chip casserole
directions: Layer crushed chips and flaked tuna.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend 30 to 60 seconds until smooth.

title: vegetable sandwich
directions: Put softened cream cheese and mayonnaise in bowl and beat with mixer until blended.
Grind vegetables and put in strainer.
Press out all juice.
Mix with cream cheese mixture (mellows with age). This will keep 5 to 6 days in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix and let set.
Will keep up to month in fridge.

title: hamburger-vegetable chowder
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Place all ingredients in a large pan and simmer until done.

title: jello punch
directions: Boil 1 quart water. Add sugar and Jell-O and dissolve. Add 3 quarts cool water and pineapple juice. Refrigerate until serving time. Add the Sprite or 7-Up.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop cucumbers, onions, green pepper and garlic cloves. Sprinkle salt over.
Cover with ice.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Drain. Put all ingredients together and bring to boiling.
Put in jars with seals.
Put in hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Purchase chicken cutlets, or prepare them yourself by skinning and boning chicken breasts.
One whole breast yields 2 cutlets. Cutlets must be pounded until thin (approximately 1/4-inch).
Use the flat side of a meat pounder, cleaver or large knife.
Sprinkle cutlets lightly with salt or pepper, if desired.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all together.
Put into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: party pizza
directions: Fry sausage; add cheese and oregano.
Drain off grease. Spread on party rye bread or on whole wheat bread and cut into fourths or shapes.
Place
on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store in Baggie. Heat at 400°.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook ziti according to box.
In a bowl, put Ricotta, parsley, 1 egg, salt and pepper, Parmesan cheese and 6 ounces of Mozzarella cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Drain ziti and rinse with cold water, return to pan and mix with ingredients. Pour half of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Add ziti mixture.
Pour remaining sauce on top and sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet, stirring constantly to keep separated.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Stir in 2 tablespoons chili powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Add grated cheese.
Cover and set aside.
Dip each tortilla in hot cooking oil for several seconds on each side, using tongs or a spatula. Do not brown or cook hard.
Place tortillas in sauce mixture, 4 to 5 at a time.
Remove 1 tortilla at a time; place in a large casserole.
Fill with 2 tablespoons beef mixture; roll tightly. Repeat until all are prepared; stack if necessary, to get all in casserole.

title: golden cauliflower
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large skillet.
Add cauliflower and water.
Cover and steam over high heat for 3 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Cover; continue steaming until cheese melts and cauliflower is tender, about 2 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add onion, parsley, rosemary and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in tomato paste and water. Layer in this order:
noodles, meat sauce and cheese.
Make 2 layers.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: ugly dip
directions: You'll need a large bowl and a food processor.

title: brownies
directions: Mix and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease round 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan or 9 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.

title: linguine florentine
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly.
Cook spinach, covered, in a large Dutch oven over medium heat about 4 minutes or until tender.
Do not add water.
Drain well; finely chop leaves and set aside.

title: dyanna's sweet rolls
directions: Roll dough into rectangle, 15 x 9-inches, on floured surface. Spread with margarine. Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over surface of dough.
Roll up tightly and pinch edges of roll to seal. Cut into nine 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place in pan. Let rise until double, about 2 to 3 hours or overnight in warm place.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Immediately invert pan onto foil.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes so drippings can absorb into rolls.

title: grandma's beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in water-soaked pot (clay).
Cover with water-soaked lid.
Microwave 15 minutes on High.
Stir well and re-cover.
Microwave 55 to 60 minutes on Medium (simmer) or until meat is tender.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach delight
directions: Combine flour and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cut into margarine until coarse and crumbly.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Press into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely. Combine peaches, sugar and lemon juice and set aside.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar and beat until fluffy.
Stir in 3 cups topping.
Spread over crust.
Combine instant pudding with peaches.
Spread over cream cheese.
Spread remaining whipped topping on next, then sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion with enough water to cover.
Add bacon when
potatoes
are
soft.
Also add grease, some water, milk, corn, eggs and pepper.

title: pickled bologna
directions: Drain gizzards.
(Broth may be saved for use in another dish.) If canning, put gizzards in jars with a slice of onion and 1 hot pepper (optional).
If refrigerating, put gizzards in large enough container and add 1 sliced onion.
Pour vinegar mixture over gizzards and refrigerate, or for canned, cover with mixture, tighten canning lids and process in pressure cooker for 30 minutes. Makes 4 jars.

title: beef and salsa biscuit bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13x9inch baking dish. Divide biscuits into quarters place in baking dish. Combine salsa, beef, chiles, peppers, and onions in a bowl. Pour over biscuits. Bake 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheddar and monterey jack cheese. Bake 10 more minutes until cheese is melted.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Beat carrots until all lumps are gone.
Add other ingredients as listed.
Pour into greased souffle dish or 2-qt. casserole dish. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until tooth pick inserted comes out clean.

title: brisket
directions: Sprinkle with liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce. Wrap brisket in heavy-duty foil. Cook 6 hours at 250°. At end of 6 hours, take out and take off fat. Use bottled barbecue sauce with onion and cook 1 hour. Cool, then refrigerate until next day and slice.

title: ghetto food
directions: In buttered casserole dish, layer drained corn, layer of ground beef (cooked and drained), layer of mashed potatoes (can be instant or real mashed potatoes).

title: ritz pie
directions: Beat egg whites with sugar, baking powder and vanilla until stiff peaks form.
Fold in crackers and walnuts.
Put in a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Place in 375° preheated oven; turn heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Whip heavy cream with a little vanilla and spread on pie.
If desired, grate German sweet chocolate on top.
You may also slice fresh strawberries on top of pie and then cover with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: mom's no-bake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Stir constantly over high heat for 5 minutes or until butter has melted.
Add peanut butter and rolled oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper or a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Allow to cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake in a 10 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 300° for 1 hour or until done.
Put icing on hot cake.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans, ham hocks, garlic powder, black pepper, salt, water and Picksweet Blend on low to medium heat until almost done. Add sausage slices and cook until beans are completely done, then add cooked rice and serve.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, chestnuts, onions, dressing and spinach.
Spread on tortillas; roll tightly and refrigerate 24 hours.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch circles.

title: elephant ears
directions: Soften yeast in the warm water.
Mix flour with sugar and salt.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter as for pastry.
Combine milk, egg yolk and yeast mixture.
Add to flour and mix well.
Cover and chill until firm enough to handle (about 2 hours).

title: triple chocolate mocha trifle
directions: Dissolve coffee granules in warm water.
Set aside.
Whisk milk into pudding mixes until thick.
Mix with coffee and water mixture until smooth.
Fold in cool whip until fluffy.
In a pretty trifle bowl, begin with a layer of 1/3 of the brownie cubes.
Top this with 1/3 of the pudding mixture.
Then sprinkle with 1/3 of the chopped Heath bars.
Repeat in this order two times.
Chill and serve.

title: lorraine's broccoli salad
directions: Mix the Miracle Whip salad dressing, garlic powder, red onion and vinegar together.
Marinate 24 hours.

title: artichoke quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie shell 7 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven to 325°.
Drain artichokes, reserving the marinade.
Saute onion and garlic in reserved marinade 5 minutes. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs and add bread crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and Tabasco.
Stir in cheese, parsley, artichokes and onion mixture.
Pour into the partially baked pie shell and bake 45 minutes.
Allow to cool 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: skillet barbecue chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in ungreased large skillet.
Combine Coke and ketchup and pour over chicken.
Cover; bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Wipe the chicken breasts with paper towels.
Sprinkle each half with salt, pepper and Accent.
Place pancake mix in paper sack, then coat each piece of chicken by shaking in sack.
Heat the oil in skillet and brown chicken.
Cook the rice according to directions on package.
Stir the soup and half and half into the cooked rice.
Put the soup and rice mixture in a buttered casserole, then put chicken pieces on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve piping hot.
Serves 6.

title: ruth's chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken; cool.
Remove from bone.
Grind all ingredients in a meat grinder.
Mix together with 1 tablespoon of vinegar and mayonnaise.
Store in refrigerator.

title: indian pudding
directions: Add corn meal gradually to scalded milk and cook in double boiler (stirring constantly) and cool 20 minutes.
Add oleo, molasses, seasonings and eggs.
Turn into buttered baking dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef tips
directions: Mix all together.
Put in baking dish and cover.
Cook 2 hours at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Pat dry.
Melt butter in frying pan over medium heat.
Stir in onion, oil, minced garlic, lemon juice and salt (if desired).
Cook until onions are done.
Add shrimp to frying pan.
Cook, stirring, until shrimp are pink.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken with some celery, onion, salt and pepper until tender; debone chicken and set aside.
Save broth.
Over medium heat, saute onion in butter; season with salt and cayenne pepper. Add soups, Cheez Whiz, 1/2 of grated cheese and chilies.
Heat until all ingredients are blended.
Soak tortillas in chicken broth.
Layer bottom of 9 x 12 x 3-inch casserole dish with tortillas.
Next, put one layer of chicken pieces, then top with sauce.
Repeat each layer.
Top off with remainder of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with onion powder, garlic powder, pepper and Cajun seasoning. Sprinkle with flour to lightly coat. Place in a large Dutch oven. Bake, covered, in a preheated 450° to 500° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. While baking, combine the remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Stir to mix well. At the end of 40 minutes, reduce oven temperature to 250°. Remove roast from oven and pour liquid mixture over roast. Cover and return to oven to bake approximately 6 hours or longer, depending on size of roast.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Drain artichokes in can and reserve liquid.
Chop finely. Chop marinated hearts and add with oil
Mix in garlic, 2-1/2 cups bread crumbs, lemon juice and cheese.
Use reserved water to moisten if too dry.
Chill mixture 1 hour;
then roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in bread crumbs.
May be served warm or cold.
To warm, heat in oven at 350 degrees for about 15 minutes.
This makes about 75 balls.

title: barbecue
directions: Begin browning meat in a large pot.
Cut vegetables to desired size.
Add remaining ingredients.
Continue cooking until meat is thoroughly cooked.
Enjoy!

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in a covered container. Use about 1/3 cup of mix to a cup of hot water or milk.

title: cajun catfish
directions: Amounts of ingredients increase with number of catfish fillets used.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt oleo in double boiler.
Combine dry ingredients and add to oleo.
Slowly add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add cheese, cut in pieces and chopped pepper.
Pour into serving dishes and serve warm with chips.

title: great granny's tea cakes(lucille hedgepeth butler)
directions: Mix 4 cups sifted flour with other ingredients until well blended.
Pour 1/2 cup flour onto cloth or rolling sheet.
Pour out dough onto cloth and knead.
Roll out dough, cut and place onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble half the box of crackers.
Pour 1/2 stick melted oleo over crackers.
Make a crust in casserole dish.
Cook noodles in chicken broth and drain.
Mix chicken, noodles, soups and sour cream.
Put in casserole dish over crackers.
Crumble other half box of crackers on top and slice 1/2 stick oleo on top.
Bake slowly until crackers are brown.

title: working woman's dinner
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs, then melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and squash.
Sift dry ingredients and add nuts and vanilla.
Butter and flour 2 small bread pans and pour in pans.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and put half of the mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: bacon sticks
directions: Dredge both sides of bacon strips in cheese and roll around bread stick diagonally.
Place bread sticks on microwave baking sheet or paper plate lined with paper towels.
Microwave at High 4 1/2 to 6 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Roll in cheese again.

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake about 30 minutes; stir.
Cover and bake about 20 minutes longer or until macaroni is tender.

title: momma's holiday dressing
directions: Bake the turkey in a browning bag with "too much salt."
Hide turkey so son won't eat all the skin.
Crumble the cornbread and crackers in large (I mean real big) bowl.
Add the celery and onions which have been chopped and cooked in water until done.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix in eggs.
Mix in juice of turkey.
Bake in all the pans you can find at about 350° or 400° until it doesn't jiggle.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle minced onion over broccoli.
Mix the 2 soups together and pour over broccoli and onion.
Mix stuffing and margarine; sprinkle on top. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Boil; drain well.
Mix egg, onion, mayonnaise, cheese and soup.
Pour over cooked broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole and cover with bread cubes.
Add melted butter. Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: frozen fruit slices(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cheese and mayonnaise or salad dressing; beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in the drained fruit cocktail, marshmallows and maraschino cherries. In small mixing bowl, whip the chilled cream until soft peaks form.
Fold the whipped cream into the fruit mixture.
Tint mixture with maraschino cherry juice, if desired.
Pour into a 12 x 7 1/2-inch dish.
Cover and freeze until firm.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa in a saucepan.
Stir in milk, margarine and corn syrup.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Boil and stir approximately 1 minute. Remove from heat; cool without stirring until the bottom of the pan is lukewarm (about 45 minutes).
Stir in vanilla and nuts, then stir in powdered sugar until mixture is very stiff.
Press into buttered loaf pan 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Refrigerate until firm (30 minutes).
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes approximately 32 candies at 80 calories each.

title: grandma couch's cranberry salad
directions: *Prepare as directed except with only 1 cup cold water and use pineapple juice as part of the cold water.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and top with crushed corn flakes (or others); pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Microwave hamburger on High until meat is set.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Microwave, covered, on High 15 to 17 minutes, or until noodles are tender, stirring often.
Sprinkle on cheese; cover until cheese is melted.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix in bowl in order given.
Let ripen in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Can be served on a lettuce leaf.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on; cool and peel off skins.
Cut potatoes into chunks or cubes.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Use a big blob of mayonnaise; gently turn ingredients over until thoroughly mixed.
Serve chilled.

title: green chile quiche
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a medium skillet until lightly browned.
Spread in pastry shell and top with green chiles and cheese.
Combine last 4 ingredients and pour over cheese and meat. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a small bowl. In a large bowl, cream the eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix the dry ingredients and creamed mixture together.
Add flour mixture slowly to this mixture.
Add the pumpkin to the previous mixture. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening till crumbly; reserve 1/2 cup. To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, soda and spices. Mix well. Add milk and eggs. Mix well.
