Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 X 1 1/2 inch round cake pans. Top with reserved crumbles. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve warm. Makes two cakes.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Lay bread slices in the bottom of a large greased casserole. Add chicken.
Mix together butter, mayonnaise, eggs, milk and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese slices and spread soup over all.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, adding all ingredients except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 jello mixture in oblong dish; let jell. Then spread with sour cream.
Pour rest of jello mixture over sour cream. Congeal.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Take 1/2 cup berries and water, bring to boil in heavy saucepan.
When berries are done, add sugar and cornstarch (dissolved in 4 tablespoons water); add salt.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add remaining berries and lemon juice.
Pour into baked pie shell, chill and serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until soft.
Dice onion, carrots and green pepper.
Mix macaroni, onion, carrots and green pepper together. Set aside while you blend with mixer, salad dressing, Pet milk, sugar, mustard and vinegar to a smooth texture.
Add to macaroni and mix well.
Drain and rinse shrimp.
Add to macaroni with celery salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well; store in airtight container in refrigerator overnight or until well chilled.
Serves between 20 and 30 people.

title: taco dip
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, cook beef, onion and pepper until meat is no longer pink; drain. Add the cheese, taco sauce and water; stir until cheese is melted. Stir in the tomato, green pepper and olives. Serve warm with chips. Yield: 6 cups.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Brown wings in butter and garlic.
When wings are almost brown, remove garlic and fry wings until completely brown. Combine other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over wings and simmer for 10 minutes over low heat.

title: cabbage-ground beef casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of cabbage in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix the next 7 ingredients together.
Spread mixture over cabbage.
Slice and cover mixture with the other 1/2 head of cabbage.
Pour tomato sauce over all; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake, covered, for 2 hours at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Stir in milk and bananas. Blend dry ingredients and stir into cream mixture.
Blend in nuts and pour into loaf pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.
Cracks in top are normal.
Cool before slicing.
Good plain or with peanut butter icing.

title: chocolate cake pudding
directions: Sift 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt together into a 9-inch square pan.
Stir in milk, margarine and vanilla.
Spread evenly in pan.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 c.
cocoa.
Sprinkle over cake batter in pan.
Pour water over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or topping, if desired.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream all ingredients together and pour in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix together above ingredients and pour over chicken wings. Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours or longer.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting with marinade.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Make pie crust; place in 9-inch pie pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Cover with second crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except pecans.
Using wet hands, shape mixture into ball.
Roll in pecan pieces.
Chill in refrigerator for 24 hours, if possible, before serving to allow flavors to blend.

title: ham-it-up cheese snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place ham slices on rectangles.
Spread ham slices with mustard and Miracle Whip. Sprinkle with cheese.
Starting at shortest side, roll up each rectangle; press edges to seal.
Coat rolls with sesame seed.
Cut each of the 4 rolls into 5 slices, forming 20 slices.
Place cut side down on greased cookie sheet (spray sheet with no-stick spray).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown. Serve warm.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together; add eggs 1 at a time, beating well.
Add flour and milk alternating, start and end with flour. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs (desired amounts of eggs) and prick the eggs several times with a toothpick.
Place eggs in a glass jar.
Use whatever size jar is necessary to hold all the boiled eggs.
Bring white vinegar and spoon of lemon juice to boil.
Pour over eggs while hot.
You can add red peppers to taste.
Seal jar and let cool.
Serves 24.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Mix the flour and salt; coat chicken pieces.
Brown chicken on both sides in hot oil about 20 minutes.
Drain on paper towel. Drain excess fat from skillet.
Return chicken to skillet; add green pepper and onion.
Mix tomato sauce, water, seasonings and mushrooms; pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice or spaghetti pasta.

title: easy delicious chicken
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; pour over chicken pieces.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes covered and 45 minutes uncovered.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Coat chicken with flour and brown in oil.
Put
in
9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes while making sauce.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa, soda and salt together.
Add, alternating with hot water.
Add dates and 1/2 of chips.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle rest of chips over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered supper
directions: Divide potatoes between two 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dishes. Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange corn and green pepper over potatoes in each casserole dish.
Layer onion and carrot in each. Crumble the beef evenly over the vegetables.
Sprinkle with more salt and pepper.
Pat gently to smooth.
Top each casserole with tomato sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 hours.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Serves 16 to 18.

title: microwave nachos
directions: Arrange Doritos on large plate.
Pour taco sauce over Doritos evenly.
Sprinkle sliced olives and grated cheese over chips. Heat in microwave 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake in prepared 325° oven for approximately 13 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing.

title: mama's chili
directions: Can use chopped hot peppers.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crumble
cookies.
Mix	Cool Whip, cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
In large bowl mix pudding with milk. Combine cream
cheese
mixture; mix well.
Use a flowerpot and put cookies
in
bottom.
Add
cream cheese mixture, cookies, cream cheese
maybe
to 4 layers; ending with cookies on top. Place plastic flower in top and serve with flower spade. (You can also use a 13 x 9-inch pan.) Keep refrigerated.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Then mash bananas.
Add (by sifting) the dry ingredients to wet mixture. Beat well.
Add chips.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring honey, Karo syrup, sugar and cream of tartar to full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and baking soda.
Mix and pour over popped corn.
Let cool somewhat and shape into balls.

title: quick italian rice soup
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add mushrooms, stewed tomatoes, 3 to 4 cups water and noodles or instant brown rice to suit your taste.
Cook according to noodles/rice directions on package. (Add seasonings now.)
Beef bouillon can be added.

title: gramma goodling's oven-apple butter
directions: Put first three ingredients in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Stir frequently.
Take out of oven; add and mix in spices.

title: low calorie homemade ice cream
directions: Mix according to your freezer's directions.
Makes approximately 14 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pear custard bars
directions: Cream butter and 1/3 cup sugar together; beat in flour, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and nuts.
Press in greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or lightly browned.
Cool. Mix cream cheese, egg, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla together and pour over crust.
Drain pears and cut into 1/8-inch slices. Arrange over filling.
Combine 1/2 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over pears.
Bake at 375° for 28 to 30 minutes.
Center will be soft, but will firm while cooling.
Refrigerate before cutting.

title: grilled packet dinners
directions: Spray foil with cooking spray.
Place potatoes, onions and carrots in the middle of a 26-inch sheet of foil.
Crumble raw ground beef over the top of vegetables and sprinkle with bouillon. Add dollops of margarine.
Lightly salt and pepper, then add ice cubes.
Fold foil over the mixture to make a sealed packet and crimp edges together on the sides and over the top.
Heat grill to medium-low.
Place packets on grill for about 1 hour.
Packets are done when beef is cooked and potatoes are tender.
A packet will serve 2.
Serve with ketchup, mustard, horseradish or other condiments, if desired.

title: oatmeal drops
directions: Sift flour and cinnamon together.
Cream sugar and shortening. Beat in eggs.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk, combining well after each addition.
Stir in oatmeal and raisins.
Drop on lightly greased baking sheet and bake in a moderate oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan.
Mix together well.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake miniatures
directions: In bowl, mix cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla, juice and salt.
Insert 24 cupcake liners in tins.
Place vanilla wafer, flat side down in liners.
Fill cups 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until filling is puffed and set.
Filling will settle back when cooled.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 24.

title: buuelos(fried cheese puffs)
directions: Grind the cheese.
Mix the cheese with the cornstarch, eggs, brown sugar and salt.
Roll into balls the size of golf balls and drop into medium-hot vegetable oil.
Fry slowly.
After a few minutes, increase temperature and fry until they are golden. Remove and place on absorbent paper.
Makes 15 buuelos.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken; cook spaghetti in chicken broth until tender and drain.
Saute chopped onion, bell pepper and pimento in butter until tender.
Mix chicken, spaghetti, vegetables and soup. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: onion mushroom rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a medium nonstick pan. Bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes. A super easy "put everything in a pan and cook" recipe.
Yields 4 servings. Has 225 calories, 1 g fat.

title: trudy's joes
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer and serve on buns.
Delicious!

title: pineapple nut chiffon pie
directions: Mix juice, milk, nuts and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts and refrigerate.
Makes two pies.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer vegetables repeating zucchini and tomato layers, sprinkling the flour or cornstarch over lower layers to thicken and to absorb some of the liquid the vegetables make as they cook.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook vegetables, covered with aluminum foil, for 30 minutes.
Remove cover after 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top to cover.
On top of this, place crushed saltine crackers to cover.
Return to oven for 30 minutes more, uncovered. Delicious when flavors meld.
Bake at 350°.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: In a saucepan, combine all except the mushrooms.
Bring to a boil and add the mushrooms.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes; cool to room temperature.
Transfer to a glass jar and cover tightly. Refrigerate 7 days before using.

title: lemon loaf(crunchy lemony goodness)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a loaf pan with margarine.

Cream sugar and margarine, add grated lemon peel and mix until smooth. Mix together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda; set aside. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture.
Do not overmix!
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into loaf pan and bake 30 to 45 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes.
In a small saucepan, combine 2 tablespoons lemon juice and 3 tablespoons sugar and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Pierce top of cake with a fork, spoon lemon-sugar mixture into holes.
Let cool for easy slicing (a whiff of lemon loaf may cause you to slice the cake warm).

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the cocktail sauce.
Form into a ball, wrap and chill.
When chilled or ready to serve, pour cocktail sauce over the ball.
Serve with party crackers.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in small amount of fat.
Add seasonings, tomato soup and water.
Combine this meat mixture and noodles.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese or cheese soup.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 2 raw pie crusts.
Bake on center rack at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Can also be frozen. Thaw before baking.

title: black bean soup
directions: Cook garlic and onion in olive oil. Mix all ingredients. Cook 1 hour or more.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Allow ice cream to soften slightly.
Mix peanut butter until soft and creamy.
Add softened ice cream gradually, mixing until blended.
Place in baked pastry shell.
Top with salted peanuts. Store in freezer several hours or until firm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, sifted with salt and baking powder.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° to 425°.

title: pork chop and scalloped potato casserole
directions: Fry pork chops and set aside.
Place a layer of potatoes and onion in bottom of baking dish or pan.
Then place layer of pork chops on potatoes.
Put 1 tablespoon of cheese on pork chops.
Put a layer of potatoes over top of chops.
Mix remaining cheese and dot top with margarine.
Pour on milk, salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tutti frutti fudge
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir just until the marshmallows are melted and mixture is well blended.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Heat oil; brown chops.
Remove.
Saute onions and chilies; stir until onions are soft and clear.
Stir in rice until lightly browned.
Add soup and water; blend well.
Place in greased casserole; top with pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: opal's lemon cheese pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add one egg at a time, beating well. Add other ingredients. Pour into uncooked pie shell (deep-dish). Cook 1 hour at 325°.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook bacon.
Drain juice off of all beans. Drain grease from meat.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into large Dutch oven and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: salso ala meretrice
directions: Saute garlic in the oil until soft; add the anchovies.
When the anchovies have broken apart, add the tomatoes; simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend in olives, capers, basil and red pepper.
Simmer in uncovered pan for 20 minutes or until sauce has thickened. Serve on capellini or vermicelli.
Don't let the anchovies turn you off.
The anchovies impart flavors but no "hairy" texture. Honest.
We usually double or triple the recipe.
We freeze it in small portions to "zap" after work.

title: quick and easy toffee bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Grind very fine, preferably in a old fashion hand grinder all of the above vegetables, and add meat and simmer for at least 5-6 hours, the longer you simmer the better the finished product. Grinding the vegetables blends the different flavors into a soup that is fit for a king.
A very old family recipe.

title: major benjamin talmadges second horse punch(for adults only)
directions: Stir thoroughly.
If ice can be obtained, pour mixture over large block in bowl.
Add 2 or 3 pints of effervescent mineral water and serve at once in cups.
tags: light bodied rum from West Indies

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Mix with sour cream, cottage cheese and onions; set aside.
Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; simmer 10 minutes.
Layer meat, then noodles mixture in casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in covered casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until beginning to get double or fluffy.
Start sprinkling sugar over whites, while continuing beating, until thick and all of sugar is used; if you tilt bowl over, it will not slide out.
Add vanilla during last of beating.
After putting meringue over pie, bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: strawberry shortcake in a bucket
directions: Follow directions on back of cake recipe box.
Pour cake batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and cook as directed; let cool. Wash strawberries and slice into a large bowl; add both jars of glaze.
Stir with a spoon.
Divide cake into 3 sections.
Get one section and crumble into bottom of bucket, forming your first layer.
The second layer will be your strawberry with glaze.
The third layer will be layer of Cool Whip.
Alternate layers until you fill your bucket (normally 3 times).
A gallon ice cream bucket is perfect for this recipe.

title: creole salad dressing
directions: Put ingredients into a wide-necked bottle and store in refrigerator.
Shake bottle vigorously just before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thickens and turns clear.
Then add Jell-O.
Let cool.
Next, add sliced strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell.
Add Cool Whip topping.

title: mint ice cream sandwiches
directions: Scoop 1/4 cup ice cream onto each of 8 cookie wafers.
Top with remaining 8 wafers and press down gently.
Swirl top of each sandwich with chocolate.
Serve immediately or wrap and freeze until ready to serve.
You may substitute any ice cream or frozen yogurt flavors.
You may also use any flavor wafer.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Line flat pan with onion soup mix (dry).
Next put layer of rice and then chicken on top of that.
Mix water and cream of chicken soup; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: Cook the onion and green pepper in large skillet over medium heat.
Stir in rice, chili powder, salt to taste, pepper, tomato sauce and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Spread on bottom of plate or platter.
Top with layers of lettuce, tomato and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Pour taco sauce on top.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together, saving 1/2 cup ketchup for topping. Place in a large loaf pan or a casserole dish. Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Pour off excess fat. Cover with remaining 1/2 cup ketchup and return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven. Serve hot.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown sirloin quickly in butter.
Push meat to side.
Add onions and mushrooms; cook until tender, but not brown.
Add salt and pepper.
Add broth and heat just to boiling.
Blend sour cream and flour well.
Stir into meat mixture, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
(Sauce will be thin.)
Add curry powder; stir well.
Cook noodles (8 ounce package) as directed; drain. Pour mixture over noodles and serve.

title: pumpkin apple soup
directions: Cook butter, onion and apples.
Simmer flour, stock and pumpkin.
Stir and cover 25 minutes.
Cool (maybe overnight). Blend smooth.
Heat up.
Mix apple juice and half and half.
Add your own spices.
Put in hollow pumpkins.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef with parsley and oregano (to taste); add sauce to warm.
Stuff noodles (do not cook noodles first) with beef/sauce mixture.
Bake in covered casserole dish at 300° to 350° for about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: fideo
directions: Heat oil in low heat.
Add uncooked vermicelli over low heat; stir until golden brown.
Add cubed steak.
Add the rest of the ingredients, simmering for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: prufrock baked squash
directions: Cut squash into cubes.
Boil until just tender.
Drain and mash, then drain again.
Combine squash, margarine, bread crumbs, seasonings and egg.
Place in lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana split pie # 2
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine. Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Mix eggs, margarine and powdered sugar.
Beat about 15 minutes; add vanilla.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Top bananas with pineapple.
Cover with container of Cool Whip.
Top with chopped pecans and maraschino cherries.
Chill before serving.
Serves 15.

title: peanut butter and jam bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour, soda and baking powder.
Reserve 1 cup of dough.
Press remaining dough in ungreased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), spread with jam.
Crumble reserved dough, sprinkle over jam.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Cool; drizzle with glaze.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt and lemon juice.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, add mayonnaise, grapes, olives, almonds and oranges last.
Mix well.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: fudge
directions: Bring to boil the first 3 ingredients; boil 6 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate chips, Hershey bars, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: chili sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients except tomato paste for 1/2 hour.
Add tomato paste; boil 1/2 hour more.

title: mousse in a minute
directions: Pour milk into bowl; add the mix.
With a whisk or electric mixer, beat at low speed until well blended, approximately 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping and spoon into dessert dishes. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Mix flour and cinnamon; reserve.
Beat margarine, corn syrup and vanilla in large bowl on medium speed until well blended. Stir in flour mixture and walnuts.
Cover; refrigerate until chilled and easy to handle, at least 3 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: one pot pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in a deep casserole (3-quart) with vegetables.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 400° about 2 hours or until tender.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with an electric mixer. Using an ice cream scoop, place meat balls onto a broiling pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown. Transfer meat balls to a glass casserole dish.

title: pink colada
directions: Mix limeade, coconut cream and grenadine syrup.
Add sparkling water.
Serve over ice and garnish with lime slice and maraschino cherry if desired.
Makes 24 servings (1/2 cup each).

title: chocolate covered candy
directions: Mix well and shape into small balls.
Melt 1/2 pound semi-sweet chocolate and 1/2 block paraffin wax.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper.

title: brownies in ice cream cones
directions: Prepare brownies according to package directions; add nuts. Fill each cone with 1/4 cup brownie batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with topping(s) about 10 minutes before end of baking time.

title: root beer float
directions: Put 2 scoops of vanilla ice cream in a large cup.
Pour in root beer.
Makes 1 serving for every 12 ounces of root beer.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch bread pan. Sift flour, sugar, baking power and salt into mixing bowl.
Make a well in the middle of sifted mixture and pour in orange juice, eggs and melted butter.
Mix well without overmixing.
Fold in walnuts, cranberries and orange rind.
Pour batter into pan and set on middle rack of oven.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let bread cool for 10 minutes.
After it's been removed from the oven, then remove bread from pan.
Bread tastes best if it is wrapped for 1 to 2 days before serving.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: avocado dip
directions: Blend until smooth.
Chill in refrigerator and serve with chips.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, from eggplant, cut 12 (1/4-inch) thick lengthwise slices; set aside.
Coarsely chop any remaining eggplant to add to sauce later.
Finely chop mushrooms and onion.
Mince the garlic.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot olive or salad oil, cook mushrooms, garlic and 3 tablespoons water until tender.
Remove mushroom mixture to large bowl.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet.
Add cauliflowerets.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add peas.
Cover and cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in pimentos, salt and pepper. Yields 8 servings.

title: easy cheesy lemon bars (or chocolate)
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients until moist.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Generously grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of pan. Mix cake mix according to directions. Pour batter over coconut and pecans. Mix together remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls over batter. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. After cake cools, cut and turn over to serve.

title: cream cheese and shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, garlic salt and onion in mixer until fluffy.
Spread on serving plate.
Pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese mixture. Spread shrimp over sauce.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and milk for 10 minutes.
After starts to boil, turn heat down and stir constantly.
Add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Beat or stir until mixed well or creamy. Pour into buttered pan and cool.
Best if cooled at room temperature.

title: frozen vanilla delight(homemade vanilla ice cream)
directions: Mix canned milk, sugar and vanilla.
Put in freezer canister. Fill canister with milk to the "full" line marked on canister. Freeze according to crank or electric mixer directions.
Gather all your friends around to enjoy!

title: 8 layer salad
directions: Layer chopped or broken lettuce in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Sprinkle chopped green onions.
Spread over chopped celery.
Pour on cooked peas.
Add layer of Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of sugar. Crumble bacon over all.
Top with 4 ounces of grated mild Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: aunt jean's corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until center is firm.

title: bell pepper relish
directions: Take the seeds from the peppers and core the apples and put through
food chopper.
Drain off the juice and mix 1 pint vinegar, 1	teaspoon salt and 3 cups sugar.
Mix and cook down until it is kind of thick.	Seal in jars. Makes about 8 pints.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cornbread crumbs.
Line bottom of large greased casserole with 2 cups crumbs.
Add squash mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 cups bread crumbs. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter to coat well.

title: 7-minute chicken casserole
directions: Combine meat, thawed vegetables, soup and milk.
Add 1 cup French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and top with remaining onions.
Serves 4 to 5. This is good for that leftover turkey after holidays.

title: christmas cocktail
directions: In a shaker, combine cranberry juice, apple juice, lemon juice, grenadine and ice.
Shake and strain into cocktail glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: sweet potato-cranberry casserole
directions: Mix together well and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
The last 5 minutes top with marshmallows.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press 1 package rolls into pan. Mix the cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, egg and almond extract. Spread on roll layer.
Top with second package of rolls.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Pour over each layer.
Cover and store in refrigerator 24 hours before eating.

title: rhubarb-strawberry preserves
directions: Mix together rhubarb and sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Mix well.
Pack in sterilized jars and cover with sterilized lids.

title: fluffy white rice
directions: Measure 2 cups water into a heavy saucepan (at least 2-quart capacity) and bring to a boil.
Add 1 tablespoon oleo and 1 teaspoon salt, if desired.
Stir in 1 cup rice.
Cover and lower heat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and all water is absorbed.
Makes about 3 cups of fluffy white rice.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Put both kinds of peppers and 1/4 cup vinegar in blender and process.
Add to sugar in large kettle.
Pour 1 cup vinegar into blender and blend briefly.
Add to pan.
Bring to boil and skim; add Certo and food coloring to tint light green.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Cool and stir for 5 minutes, skimming if necessary.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.
Makes approximately 6 half-pint jars of jelly.
Serve with crackers and cream cheese.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco well.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add, alternating with milk to creamy mixture.
Add flavoring.
Pour into a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
This makes a large cake (10-inches).

title: baked chicken with fruit
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix first four ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and add pineapple.
Bake for 30 more minutes.

title: mexican beef'aroni(a microwave recipe)
directions: Microwave:
Brown
beef
in plastic colander for 5 to 6 minutes on	Full
Power
(or
brown in 2 quart casserole dish, then drain).
Mash	beef
to remove chunks; add other ingredients except
cheese
and chips.	Stir well.
Cover and cook 11 to 12 minutes
on
Full
power.
Stir 3 times during cooking. Let stand 5 minutes, add cheese and chips, then serve.

title: glazed raspberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine 2/3 cup raspberries and 2/3 cup water. Simmer, uncovered, for 3 minutes. Strain raspberries and discard seeds; set juice aside.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind vegetables coarsely.
Add salt; let set overnight. Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to vegetables.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Put into hot sterilized jars.
Process 15 minutes.
Very good!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef, then drain it.
Pour in 16 ounces of tomatoes, your green pepper, diced onion, basil and salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup and cooked noodles.
Pour all in baking dish; put cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Put in oven until cheese melts and bread crumbs are hard.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, fruit cocktail, peaches and cherries.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: fruitcake
directions: Keep out a portion of flour and use it to dredge fruit. Prepare batter and add fruit mixture to batter.
Line greased pans with paper (waxed, brown or foil) and grease again.
Bake at 250° from 3 to 5 hours, depending on size of pans.

title: connie's corn
directions: Prepare corn bread mix; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix all remaining ingredients.
Add corn bread mixture and mix again. Place in large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: chicken snacks
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Add butter and mix well.
Beat egg with 1 teaspoon water in a separate bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture and then crumb mixture. Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes, turning halfway through baking.
Makes 3 dozen appetizers.

title: chili
directions: You will need crock-pot.

title: butterscotch cream(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and egg yolks thoroughly in a saucepan. Stir i until smooth a mixture of Pet milk and water. Add butter or margarine. Cook and stir over low heat until thickened, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Cover and cool thoroughly.
Put into a cool 9 inch baked pastry shell.
Spread with meringue. Bake as directed for meringue.
Cool thoroughly before cutting with a wet knife.

title: no egg vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine sugar and condensed milk.
Add Pet milk and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add vanilla.
Pour into ice cream freezer and fill to mark with milk.
Pack with ice and salt.
Freeze.

title: old-fashioned jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add water and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Pour batter in pan lined with wax paper that has been greased (Pam and wax paper).
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Add remaining raw vegetables.
Saute 10 minutes.
Add 6 cups water, beans, tomatoes, chickpeas, herbs and salt.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add macaroni and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Season with cayenne to taste.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Good on a cold, frosty day.

title: pickled pears
directions: Peel pears.
Place in a boiler, covering with vinegar and water.
Add 2 cups water to each cup of vinegar, 1 cup of sugar to each or sweeten to taste.
Add pickling spice mixed.
Boil until pears are tender.

title: garbage dip
directions: Mix ingredients, serve with tortilla chips. (I double or triple this recipe.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden. Serves 4.

title: crusty brown rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve.
Add sugar, shortening and 2 cups flour; beat well.
Add beaten egg whites. Add remaining flour until dough leaves sides of bowl when your stir it.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until dough is smooth and elastic and tiny blisters show in surface, about 5 minutes.
Place in a lightly greased bowl; turn dough over to grease top.
Cover with a damp cloth and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Let rise again until doubled, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick meat sauce over rice
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Stir the cornstarch into the V-8 juice and pour over the hamburger.
Add the bouillon cube and salt.
Cook for 8 minutes or until thickened.
Place rice in a large serving bowl.
Make a hollow in the center and pour in the meat sauce.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 scoops mix per mug. Makes 17 cups of mix.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle sugar, nutmeg and lemon juice over apples.
Toss gently.
Gently mix in remaining ingredients.
Chill well and serve.

title: pasta supreme salad
directions: Peel and cut broccoli into chunks.
Cook in boiling, salted water just until tender-crisp.
Drain and rinse under cold water; drain.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package.
Drain.
Cook creamed spinach (follow package directions).
Empty spinach pouches into large bowl and cool.
Stir in Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella, salt and pepper.
Stuff each shell with tablespoon of cheese mixture.
Put shells in casserole dish and pour sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup chocolate chips.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from oven. Immediately sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Spread.
Sprinkle colored sugar over melted chocolate. Cool in pan on wire rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen bars.

title: marni's barbecued tandoori chicken
directions: Mix marinade ingredients well in a bowl or blender.
Marinate chickens for 8 to 24 hours.
Cover chickens thoroughly.
Barbecue over medium-hot grill until done.

title: virginia pickle
directions: Peel cucumbers, slice and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain well.
Slice onions, pour boiling water over them and let stand for 24 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook these with cucumbers and onions 20 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all together and place into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Place chicken in a casserole dish, salt and pepper to taste. Saute onion in margarine or microwave for 1 minute.
Add to soup in a separate bowl.
Dissolve boullion cube in water (microwave 5-6 minutes).
Add to soup mixture.
Add soy sauce and celery seed to mixture.
Pour over chicken.
Cook about 15 minutes on High or until done.
Time will vary by chicken piece size and oven wattage.
Serves 4.

title: orange carrot salad
directions: Place carrots in medium bowl.
Section oranges into the bowl to catch juices.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick of oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together except potato chips and spoon into the pan. Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 375°. Serves 8.

title: pirate pie
directions: Brown beef; drain grease.
Add bell peppers, beans, tomatoes and sauce.
Let simmer while mixing corn bread.
Pour meat mixture in large casserole dish.
Spoon corn bread on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until corn bread is done.

title: marilynn's corn pudding bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together right in 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° until slightly brown and set in center.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Grate cheese and combine with sausage.
Add Bisquick and work with hands until combined.
Add pepper and shape into balls.
Bake at 50° for 15 minutes.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add garlic and saute.
Add carrot, pepper, mushrooms and pea pods; stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes.
Add chicken, onions, teriyaki and soy sauce.
Cook just until heated through. Add broth and bring to a boil; stir in pineapple.
Dissolve cornstarch in reserved juice.
Add to skillet and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with hot cooked rice!

title: chruscini
directions: Cream sugar, egg yolks, salt, brandy and vinegar.
Add flour, roll out very thin.
Slice into oblong rectangles about 1 x 3-inches.
Slit centers and twist through.
Fry in deep fat fryer until they turn a cream color.

title: oliebollen
directions: Make a batter of the liquid, yeast, salt and flour.
Add the fruits and lemon juice; let stand and rise in a warm place under a damp cloth for 1 hour or a little longer.
Drop by tablespoons into hot Crisco and cook or fry until done, golden brown, turning once.
These are to be eaten by dipping in brown sugar or you can eat them plain.
Best when warm.

title: mochea
directions: Mix and make into balls and wrap in cabbage leaves and pin with toothpick.
Drop into boiler of broth containing 1 can tomatoes, 2 tablespoons of cooking oil and enough water to cover meatballs.
Add salt to taste and simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: aunt velma's mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well in a large mixing bowl.
I bake mine in one 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and a 9-inch skillet.
Bake at 450° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: delicious yellow cake layers
directions: Separate egg yolks and whites; beat egg whites really stiff. In separate bowl, cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in egg whites.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350°.
Ice with favorite icing.

title: sharon's mexican salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and chill.
When you are ready to serve, add the bag of Doritos (crushed).
Pour the Catalina French dressing over salad and toss.
Serve cold.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pink salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
into
hot water; add cream cheese that has been
mixed with mayonnaise.
Add mashed banana and pine-apple. Add coconut and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine cranberries, apples,
sugar and water in saucepan. Boil until sugar dissolves and berries pop open.
Remove from stove and add lemon rind.
Chill.
Makes 1 quart.

title: boneless beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in foil.
Put everything, except barbecue sauce, on meat.
Wrap tightly and place in refrigerator overnight.
Cook at 275° for 5 hours.
Uncover and drain.
Pour barbecue sauce over brisket, cover and cook 1 hour longer.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple and dry jello together. Refrigerate for a short time.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a crock-pot.
Heat on low, stirring often, until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread berries or other fruit over batter. Sprinkle 1 cup of sugar over fresh fruit (less if fruit is pre-sweetened).
Pour 1 cup boiling water over all.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar.
Cream butter.
Add eggs, bananas and lemon juice.
Stir to combine ingredients, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer or 300 strokes by hand.
Stir in 3/4 cup nuts.

title: garlic olives
directions: Split olives slightly.
Place in large jar with remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and shake.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: fried rice and shrimp
directions: Place hot oil, salt and pepper in heavy skillet (wok).
Add eggs.
Fry until firm.
Cut eggs into small strips.
Add shrimp and onions.
Stir over moderate heat for 5 minutes.
Add rice, soy sauce and sugar.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until rice is hot.

title: escalloped zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini in 1/4-inch pieces.
Place in shallow pan.
Top each with 1 slice onion and tomato.
Melt butter.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover.
Place sliced Mozzarella cheese on top.
Mix remaining melted butter with bread crumbs and drizzle over cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Fry bacon with onion.
Combine rice with half and half cream. Combine with soup and cheese.
Mix all ingredients and heat on low until cheese melts.
Makes 15 cups or 8 bowls.

title: venison camp chili texas style
directions: Combine onion, 1 can of chili beans, Tabasco, chili pepper, celery, stewed tomatoes and sugar.
Simmer for 1 hour in a large pot.
Brown venison with 1/2 onion; drain liquid.
Add to the sauce and cook at low heat for an additional hour.
Add the remaining chili beans and chili powder.
Cook at low heat for another hour.
Makes 4 to 6 hearty servings.

title: butter sauce for pound cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Gradually add water; add margarine and bring to a boil.
Cook until thick.
Add flavoring. Serve hot over slices of pound cake.

title: macadamia nut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients except whipped cream.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake for another 30 minutes.
Serve ringed with whipped cream.

title: chicken vegetable dijon
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, stir soup, mustard, oregano, pepper and milk together until smooth.
Spoon 1 cup soup mixture over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: surprise - surprise
directions: Mix strawberry preserves and horseradish together.
Pour over block of cream cheese.
Serve on crackers.

title: peanut butter banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups or use paper baking cups.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and baking powder.
Whisk together the milk, peanut butter, bananas, egg, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened. Fill prepared muffin cups 3/4 full.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over batter.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Pour a thin layer of batter in greased iron skillet.
Add cheese.
Pour in remaining batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Watch while baking, as time can vary.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, salt and oleo into crumbs and remove 3/4 cup for top.
Mix 2 cups boiling water with molasses.
Mix baking soda with 1/4 cup boiling water and add to molasses mixture.
Mix all things together by hand.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: jennifer's fruit salad
directions: Mix up and put in refrigerator for at least an hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine to a very firm soft ball stage, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until blended and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Mix wet ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour onto hot skillet.
Makes for 4 people.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cream well.
Next, add dry ingredients.
Drop mixture on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix together the first six ingredients.
Take out 3/4 cup and set aside.
To this 3/4 cup, add cinnamon and pecans.
To other, add buttermilk, soda and egg.
Beat well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 3/4 cup mixture to top of batter.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the first 6 items.
Mix together the sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs and mix well, then stir in pumpkin. Add dry ingredients alternately with cream sherry, mixing well, then add nuts.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour or when toothpick in center comes out clean.
Turn out on wire rack to cool.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate until ready to slice.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and bake 45 minutes.
While casserole bakes, grate enough Cheddar cheese to cover top and return to oven and melt cheese.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Pour cold mixture over pickles.
Pack in jars.
Leave in refrigerator for 5 days before eating.
Will keep up to 9 months refrigerated.

title: filling balls
directions: Spread cubes on a tray and season with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and celery.
Simmer for 1/2 hour, until cooked soft.
Pour over cubes and work in.
Beat egg with 1/4 cup milk and work into cubes.
Form into balls and use extra milk until mixture will pack.
(The Filling Balls should be slightly larger than a golf ball.) Pack Filling Balls in doubled foil packages and seal tightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. About halfway through cooking, turn packages over for even baking.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Set oven at 325°.
Grease and flour 2 small loaf pans.
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Gradually beat in oil and sugar; fold in zucchini.
Add vanilla and mix lightly.
In separate bowl, mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nuts and raisins.
Add to zucchini mixture and mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 small loaves.

title: apple crisp
directions: In an 8x8 baking dish, layer apples on bottom.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle evenly over the apples.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour Melted butter over top.

title: basil carrots
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter; add carrots.
Sprinkle with salt and basil.
Cover; simmer 10 to 12 minutes, just until carrots are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: harvest pumpkin loaf
directions: Place in 1 large or 3 small greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked cod fillets
directions: Combine pepper, lemon juice and onion powder in blender.
Run at medium speed for 2 minutes or until pureed.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over fish and bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
Serves 2.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix together milk, sugar and flour.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan first the butter (melted) then milk, flour and sugar mixture and fruit last.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown on top.

title: cheese bread
directions: Beat egg; add milk.
Pour into Bisquick.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Mix well and spread in a bread pan.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: "better than sex"
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix, stir until thick.
Spread on top of cheese layer.
Cover with remaining Cool whip and sprinkle with remaining pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix in a pot, the brown sugar, butter and flour.
Cook on slow heat until the mixture gets slightly brown.
Add the milk and continue cooking until it thickens.
Add the vanilla.
Let cool and put in a pie crust.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, saute the onions and green pepper in margarine.
Add the chuck and cook until chuck loses red color.
Add tomatoes, water, tomato sauce, sugar, salt and pepper. Spoon this over the uncooked noodles.
Cover with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: fondant
directions: Combine powdered sugar, butter, milk, pecans and coconut.
Roll into small balls and chill.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into mixture.
Yields about 100 servings.

title: dill weed crackers
directions: In paper bag add crackers, oil, dressing and dill weed, then shake to absorb the oil.
Store in a tight container.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Freeze Reese's peanut butter miniatures for several hours before using.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice the cookie dough. Roll into nine 1-inch slices and then quarter each slice for 36 pieces in all.
Spray 3 mini muffin pans with Pam.
Drop one piece into each muffin cup.
Do not pat or mold dough.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Soak raisins in water for 5 minutes; do not drain.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in pumpkin, sugar, cloves, cinnamon and salt; add oil, mixing well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda; add to pumpkin mixture with 1/2 of the raisin water.
Mix well.
Add remaining raisin mixture; stir to mix.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° until top springs back when pressed (about 25 minutes).
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: shade sipper
directions: Combine milk and ice cream in blender.
Add bananas.
Cover; process on low, adding 1 ice cube at a time.
Process on high for 60 seconds, or until mixture is thickened and ice is completely processed.
Pour and serve.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in large bowl.
In a medium saucepan, add the soup and milk with half a can of water.
Stir to blend.
Add the cheese and heat until melted.
Add the green onions, mushrooms and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add slightly beaten eggs to potatoes and mix well.
Pour into sprayed 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove cover and bake 25 more minutes.
Save some of the cheese to place on top of the casserole.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake at 350°, 1 hour.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Melt margarine.
Dampen toast with hot water, beat egg, add this and butter, salt, pepper and sage to the bread.
Mix well and add onions.
Stuff bird and grease outside of bird.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until done.

title: velvet cream pie
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt. Add 1 cup milk and mix until smooth.
Bring to boil over medium heat. Stir briskly.
Boil 2 minutes until smoothly thickened.
Remove from heat.

title: cherry salad
directions: Put pie filling, sugar and water on stove and boil 5 minutes. Dissolve Jell-O in hot mixture.
Add other ingredients and chill overnight.

title: laundry starch fingerpaint and window paint
directions: Dilute laundry starch in cupful of cold water.
Add remaining water.
Slowly stir to avoid lumps.
Stir in soap flakes and talcum (as a binder).
Add color with tempura paint.
Makes 5 pints.
Works as fingerpaint; over wax crayon; on glass.

title: hot banana peppers
directions: Pack hot peppers in jars with the ends of peppers cleaned and the ends sliced so syrup will go in peppers. Bring syrup mixture to rolling boil.
Pour over peppers slowly.
Put on lids tight to seal.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in the bottom of pan.
Sprinkle vanilla and cinnamon on peaches.
Put flour, sugar, baking powder, 2 tablespoons margarine and 1 egg, beaten, over the peaches.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes, then drain.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Fill paper cups 2/3 full.

title: shaggy dogs
directions: Heat syrup in opened can.
Toast marshmallows until golden brown.
Dip marshmallows in chocolate and roll in coconut.

title: belgian crepes
directions: Mix flour, salt, oil and eggs.
Add slowly water, milk and vanilla extract.
If the mix is too thick, add milk.
Mix should be liquid not thick like pancake mix.
Cook one crepe at a time, on both sides in a greased pan.
Serve crepe with jelly, powdered sugar, brown sugar or cheese and ham.
Roll it.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Beat egg, sugar and flour together; add mixture with pineapple juice.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Set aside to cool.
Mix pineapple with chopped banana, cheese and apple.
Mix with dressing mixture.

title: honey bun
directions: Put 1/3 cup of sugar in the yeast, then add to the warm milk and set aside for about 5 minutes.
Mix the rest of the dry ingredients together, then add shortening and egg; mix well.
Add the milk mixture a little at a time until the dough pulls away from the bowl.
Put a little melted butter on top of the dough.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Add oil and sweetener and mix until light.
Beat eggs and add, then add rest of ingredients. Beat until well mixed.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bar-b-que sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and heat.
Good with hot dogs and meatballs.

title: pecan turtles
directions: Cook milk and syrup until soft ball stage. Stir all the time. Put 3 pecans on sprayed pan arranged all over pan.
Drop mixture by teaspoon on nuts.
Chill.
Dip in melted
chocolate bark.
Put on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hours or on high for 4 hours.

title: sun-drop pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and margarine together.
Add sugar and mix well, then add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and Sun-Drop alternately then add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemon parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, garlic powder and parsley.
Wash chicken and leave wet.
Dip and coat both sides of chicken in bread crumb mixture.
Place in a shallow pan or casserole.
Pour melted margarine and lemon juice (mixed together) over chicken. Bake, covered, for about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrot surprise
directions: Cook carrots until half done.
Boil soup, vinegar, oil, sugar and mustard.
Add carrots, onion and pepper; set overnight in refrigerator.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until light and foamy.
Combine sugar and baking powder.
Add slowly to egg whites.
Continue beating until whites are stiff.
Fold in crackers and pecans.
Bake in greased pie pan (grease rim) at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip as served.

title: nana edna's brown edge wafers
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat again until smooth.
Sift flour and salt and add a portion at a time, beating to blend.

title: pineapple glazed carrots
directions: Use 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and salt in the pan.
Mix carrot liquid and pineapple syrup and add gradually to cornstarch mixture, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook about 3 minutes or until the liquid is thick and clear.
Stir in butter or margarine.
Add carrots and pineapple. Heat thoroughly.
Serves 4 to 5 people.
Take 15 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes. Cut into 4 x 5-inch pieces.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Top with 2 handfuls of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Combine next 5 ingredients; add to pumpkin mixture.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 8-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and on top.

title: spinach chicken pie
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole, combine stuffing mix, oats, spinach and broth.
Toss with butter and salt.
Press gently into 9-inch glass pie plate.
Cook on High in microwave for 2 minutes to set crust.
Mix chicken, sour cream, mushroom soup, 1/4 teaspoon salt and Accent and pour into center of pie shell.
Cook in microwave on High for 10 minutes, giving pie plate a quarter turn twice.
Let rest for 10 minutes before cutting into wedges for serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar; beat in egg.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix this well and press into an ungreased baking dish (up all sides and along the bottom).

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.
Drain juice from canned fruit.

title: mexican salad
directions: Drain and wash beans. Chill beans, lettuce, onion, cheese and tomatoes.
Just before serving, add crushed Doritos and dressing.

title: yeast bread
directions: Warm milk.
Add all ingredients, except flour (only use 3 cups now).
Stir.
Add milk; beat until smooth.
Add 2 1/2 cups more flour; mix.
Pour out on floured surface and knead.
Add more flour, to get slightly slick ball.
Knead about 4 to 5 minutes. Put into greased bowl; let raise about 1 1/2 hours.
Separate into 3 pieces; roll each until rectangular.
Roll up and put on greased cookie sheet.
Slit 1/4-inch deep across loaf.
Let raise 1 hour, or until double in size.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix the meats, onion, bread crumbs, egg, sage, salt and pepper in a bowl. Roll into meatballs, fry and brown.
Pour soups and milk over meatballs in a casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Great served over mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: cheese ball
directions: Knead ingredients together and mold into ball.
Put the 4 slices of pastrami across top in strips.

title: golden pheasant
directions: Brown floured pieces of bird in oil (salt with a little garlic.)

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: raspberry poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in 13 x 9-inch sheet cake pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Spray pan with Pam before baking.)
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Then poke cake with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water, and spoon over cake in pan.
Chill 3 to 4 hours. (Best when sets overnight.)
Top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: catsup
directions: Cook until thick.
Remove celery and onions when done.

title: spinach-bacon deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Scoop out yolks into a small mixing bowl and mash with a fork; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg white halves.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Combine rice, hamburger and egg.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown on all sides in a well-greased skillet; drain.
Mix seasoning packet with hot water and pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, then boil without stirring 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in baking soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popcorn and mix well.
Put in shallow baking dish or roaster; bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove from oven and break apart.

title: sour milk pancakes
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Add milk and stir lightly. Add butter and fold in eggs.
Bake on hot, ungreased griddle.

title: salmon spread
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Spread in low dish.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat pumpkin (very important).
Combine sugar, flour, salt and spices.
Add to hot pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until set.
May cover edges of unbaked pie shell with foil to keep from getting too brown. Makes 1 big and 1 small pie.

title: deluxe banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk well; fold in yogurt (or sour cream substitute) and whipped topping, which has been whipped as directed.
Layer in 13 x 15-inch pan with vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Sprinkle wafer crumbs on top for garnish, if desired.
Can be enjoyed by dieters and diabetics.

title: sweet carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook rolling 20 minutes.
Simmer remaining time to 2 hours or until tender.

title: taco bake
directions: Fry tortillas in hot oil until crispy.
Set aside.
Brown the meat and onions together in a skillet.
Add the corn and simmer for 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Boil the water & add the seasoning mix, tomato sauce and 2 tbsp.
mexican
hot sauce.
Stir
while simmering for 15 minutes.
Put 1/4 cup of the sauce in the bottom of a 2 quart casserole dish.
Break the tortillas and arrange in a layer to cover bottom of dish.
Layer on the meat, then chili beans, then sauce, then tortillas to fill the dish, ending with meat on top.
Pour in the remaining sauce.
Cover with cheese and sprinkle with olives over top if desired.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dump it cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Mix flour, milk and sugar. Pour mixture over margarine. Do not stir.
Pour fruit over batter. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together with
spoon
all ingredients.
Roll into 2 balls. Roll in crushed pecans.

title: pasta with asparagus and shrimp
directions: Cook pasta in saucepot or boiling water on stove following package directions.

title: chart house mud pie
directions: Crush wafers and add butter. Mix well.
Press into 9-inch pie plate. Cover the soft coffee ice cream.
Put into freezer until ice cream is firm. Top with cold fudge sauce.
Return to freezer for at least 10 hours before serving.
Slice Mud Pie into eight portions and serve on a chilled dessert plate with a chilled fork. Top with whipped cream and slivered toasted almonds.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Boil slowly 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add confectioners sugar.
Beat until smooth.

title: butterfingers
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll in the shape of a finger. Bake at 350° until golden in color.
While still warm, roll in granulated sugar.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: mary's hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, flour and sugar; stir in cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix crumbs with melted margarine and spread over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Boil 4 to 6 chicken breasts in water, 1-inch above meat with margarine, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add more water, if needed, to keep 4 cups broth.
Skin and debone chicken.
Dice meat.
Set aside.
Mix together chicken soup with broth.
Add diced meat and mix with stuffing.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: hershey's rich cocoa fudge
directions: Butter an 8 or 9-inch square pan and set aside.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan combine sugar, cocoa and salt; stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a rolling boil (a rolling boil cannot be stirred down).
Boil without stirring to 234° (soft-ball stage) or until syrup when dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110°.
Beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread into prepared pan to cool.
ENJOY!

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and peppers.
Mix soups, sauce, spices, celery and milk in with beef and vegetables.
Layer in casserole (rectangular) dish:
tortillas, mix, cheese and repeat.
Bake approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: millionaire pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavoring and beat well.
Bake at 325° in a large tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix coconut, nuts and milk together.
Roll into balls and freeze.
Dip balls into melted chocolate.
Spoon onto waxed paper. Let cool.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Let cheeses and oleo come to room temperature.
Mix together and set aside.
Cook shells only until firm and drain.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture and place in large baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over shells.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot cider
directions: Heat apple juice, cloves and cinnamon over medium heat until juice is piping hot; do not boil.
Serve at once.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Beat egg yolks and add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in sugar.
Let cool.
Beat egg whites.
Fold into chocolate mixture and then fold in Cool Whip.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, salt, baking powder and nuts.

title: brussels sprouts veronique
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts in large amount of boiling salted water until almost tender, about 7 minutes.
Drain and rinse under cold water; drain again.
(Can be prepared several hours ahead to this point.)
Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in grapes and Brussels sprouts and heat through.
Turn sprouts into bowl and serve.
Serves 8.

title: crab and pea salad
directions: In a bowl, mix peas, crab meat and bacon. Mix onion powder and mayonnaise. Fold into crab mixture. Cover and refrigerate until served. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl combine peas, beans, corn, onion, celery and pimientos.
In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sliced baked cheese potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices (but not all the way through).
Put potatoes in dish and spread open.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for 10 to 15 more minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Combine 1 1/2 envelopes of salad dressing mix, butter and 2 teaspoons hot pepper sauce.
Measure 1/4 cup of the mixture and reserve.
Place chicken wings in a shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining dressing mixture over chicken and toss to coat well. Let stand 15 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Chop bacon coarsely. Saute in a large kettle until almost crisp. Add onion.
Cook about 5 minutes. Add potatoes, salt, pepper and 1 cup water.
Cook, uncovered, 15 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Drain clams, reserving liquid. Add clams, 1/2 cup clam liquid, half and half and margarine to kettle. Mix well.
Heat 3 minutes. Do not boil. Serves 4.

title: potato bacon soup
directions: Spray a 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion and bacon.
Stir over medium heat until onion is tender, not brown.
Stir in water and potatoes; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Slightly mash some of the potatoes.
Stir in evaporated milk, butter seasoning, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until heated through.
Do not boil.
Yields 6 servings, each containing 181 calories, 2 grams fat and 391 milligrams sodium.

title: cottage cheese pesto
directions: In food processor, process nuts and garlic until finely chopped.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed; whirl until basil and parsley are very finely chopped, scraping down sides of bowl as needed.
Transfer to a small bowl or jar with tight fitting lid.
Place plastic wrap directly on surface of pesto. Refrigerate up to 2 days.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Toss with 1 pound cooked, drained pasta or serve over baked potatoes or tender-crisp cooked vegetables.

title: lemon-mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan. In a small saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in mustard, lemon juice, tarragon and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Bake chicken for 45 minutes, or until cooked through.

title: cheese ball or logs
directions: Mix well.
Wet hands in water and shape into logs or balls. Roll in nuts; keep refrigerated.
Makes 2 medium sticks or 1 big ball.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Combine milk and peanut butter in a bowl; blending well.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or at low speed of a electric mixer for 1 minute.
Pour into pie shells instantly and cool for 2 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook 5 minutes and drain well.

title: bran muffins
directions: Boil water; add soda and let cool.
In separate bowl, add remaining ingredients.
Combine.
Add cooled water and soda mixture.
This will keep in fridge for up to 6 weeks.
Makes about 50 muffins.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: cheeseburger macaroni
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add soup and milk.
Cut 4 to 6 slices of cheese, add and stir until melted.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Snip bacon into small pieces; saute until crisp in large skillet.
Stir in vinegar, water, sugar, salt, onion and egg. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Wash and drain lettuce. Tear into small pieces.
Toss with hot dressing in skillet.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Stir with mixer on low speed. Add 1 cup nuts and pinch of salt. Refrigerate overnight. Cover with Cool Whip and add remaining 1/2 cup pecans.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, butter and milk or cream and mix until well combined and fluffy.
In a separate bowl combine dry ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients with potato mixture and gently knead or stir until a soft dough forms.
(Add extra cream if necessary.)
Pat or roll the dough to a thickness of 1/3 to 1/2 inch.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until done.

title: miniature amaretto cakes
directions: Generously grease and flour six 4-inch fluted tube pans or one 6-cup fluted tube pan.
Let butter and eggs stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter with electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium-high speed, adding the 3/4 cup sugar 2 tablespoons at a time, about 6 minutes or until mixture is very light and fluffy. Stir in the 1/4 cup Amaretto, lemon peel and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 1 minute after each addition, scraping bowl often.
Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, beating on medium-low speed just until combined.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes for the 4-inch pans (40 to 45 minutes for the 6-cup fluted pan) or until a toothpick inserted near the center(s) comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from cake pans.
Cool thoroughly on racks. Prick fluted top and sides of each cake generously with tines of a fork.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Add boiling water to cornmeal; be sure water is boiling. Let cornmeal mixture get cold before using. You can form patties or roll into cigar shapes. Fry in about 1-inch of oil. Fry about 4 minutes on each side.

title: brownies
directions: Line square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, with aluminum foil, leaving 1-inch of foil overhanging on opposite sides. Mix powdered sugar, margarine, 1 cup peanut butter and the vanilla in large bowl. Stir in cracker crumbs and peanuts (mixture will be stiff). Press in pan.

title: tuna roll
directions: With hands, mix all ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in parsley and/or chopped nuts.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill overnight.
Serve with butter-type crackers.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Mix vanilla wafer crumbs, margarine and 1 tsp Equal.
Reserve 1 Tbsp crumb mixture.
Pat remaining mixture evenly on bottom and 1/2 inch up side of spring form pan.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven until crust is lightly browned,
about 8 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Reduce oven temperature to 300 degrees.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Peel zucchini; slice into 1/4-inch slices and beat egg and water.
Add 1 teaspoon seasoned salt; beat well.
Put biscuit mix into plastic bag with 1 teaspoon seasoning; shake well.
Heat 1/4-inch oil in frying pan; dip slices of zucchini into egg wash, then into biscuit mix in bag.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with sour cream on side.

title: english muffin loaf
directions: Set aside 2 cups flour.
In a large bowl, combine remaining flour (3 cups), sugar, salt, soda and yeast.
Heat liquids until very warm.
Add to dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in reserved flour to make stiff batter (up to 1 cup extra flour may be used to form stiff batter).
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 or 9 x 5-inch loaf dishes that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal. Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Let rise for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Slice and toast to serve.
Enjoy!

title: poppy seed oat bran muffins with orange glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
(For dark nonstick pans, preheat oven to 425°).
Grease muffin cups.

title: pork roast dinner
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix rosemary, garlic, salt and pepper and mash to paste.
Rub roast with herb garlic paste.
Roast, uncovered, basting 2 or 3 times with pan juices, for 1 1/4 hours, adding vegetables as desired.
Or wrap in heavy foil and cook on grill.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve with crackers.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind up all vegetables; add handful of salt, let stand 2 hours.
Cook 15 minutes. Drain off 2 pints of water.
Add mustard, sugar, vinegar, turmeric and flour.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Cold pack for 15 minutes.

title: ham scallopini
directions: Mix flour with salt and pepper.
Brown ham, green pepper and onion in butter; add in flour and continue to brown a bit.
Pour water into soup; mix and add into ham mixture.
Simmer until done. Stir in cheese until melted.
Good served on rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 5 minutes; drain water.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese, onion and some pepper.
Place broccoli into greased casserole dish.
Add remaining blended ingredients and slightly mix together.
Dot with butter and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp and spaghetti - yum!!!
directions: Buy cooked shrimp pieces at the deli.
Heat up Classico sauce. Cook your favorite pasta.
Add shrimp for 3 or 4 minutes.
Serve sauce and shrimp over pasta.

title: pasta with garlicky white beans and spinach
directions: Chop spinach and set aside. In large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat. When hot, add the garlic and red pepper flakes. Saut one minute.

Add the undrained tomatoes, basil, oregano, salt and pepper. Simmer 5 minutes. Stir in spinach and continue simmering for another minute. Add drained white beans and mix well. Keep warm. Cook pasta according to directions.
Mix pasta with sauce. Put into serving bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine broccoli and onion in glass bowl.
Microwave, covered, on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until broccoli thaws.
Add cottage cheese, butter and eggs; mix well.
Add muffin mix; stir just until moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 9 servings.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat together buttermilk, milk and egg.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir.
Bake on moderately hot griddle.

title: peanut butter fudge
