directions: In a saucepan (medium) combine sugar, milk and corn syrup, stirring constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage or 236° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until smooth.
Cool 15 minutes.
Beat with mixer until thick. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool 2 to 3 hours, then cut into squares.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes, celery and onion in the water in a covered pan until very tender (do not drain).
Press vegetables through a sieve.
Add milk, bouillon cubes and butter.
Mix sour cream and flour until smooth.
Add to soup and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bouillon cubes are dissolved.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger, broken up into small pieces.
Cool.
Put in bowl with lettuce, cut into small pieces.
Add tomato, cut into small pieces.
Mix.
Don't put in chips or dressing until ready to serve.
Keep in refrigerator.
Mix all together with clean hands.

title: cheese rings
directions: *Softened to room temperature.

title: different cranberry cake
directions: Put everything into a large bowl (except cranberries) and beat 4 minutes.
Carefully fold in cranberry sauce, crumbled.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 60 minutes.
May be drizzled with glaze and almond extract added or served plain with ice cream or dusted with confectioners sugar.

title: fruit 'n yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt and fruit into Cool Whip, blending well. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm (about 4 hours). Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator 30 minutes before cutting. Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: combination vegetable dish
directions: Mix thawed vegetables with soup and cheese.
Spoon into casserole dish.
Top with crumbled onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together softened butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs. Beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg or cinnamon. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Place on rack and cool before serving.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven.
Grease and flour rectangular pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, egg and sugar and drop by tablespoons onto cake batter.
Cut through batter with knife several times to give marbled effect.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts if desired.
Bake until cake springs back when touched.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: the ultimate sweet potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes; dry, butter and wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool; unwrap.
Peel and place potatoes in mixing bowl.
Mix with softened stick of butter, orange juice, half the can of Coco Lopez, brown sugar, zest and salt and pepper.
Place in a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Allow to cool.

title: frozen pops
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water, stir and pour into small paper cups or popsicle molds. Insert wooden stick or plastic spoons diagonally.
Freeze until firm, 2 to 3 hours.
Makes about 18 pops.

title: condensed milk fruit cake
directions: Mix together and bake in a loaf pan for 1 hour at 250°.

title: no sugar chocolate mousse(low carb)
directions: Add all ingredients together, beating with a mixer until it is light and fluffy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare beans according to package and drain.
Prepare stuffing mix according to box except add 1/2 cup more water.
Put green beans in bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken.
Add remaining 1/2 cup of water to soup and heat.
Pour soup evenly over chicken and beans.
Spread stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Last 5 minutes sprinkle onion rings over dish.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt chocolate and 2 tablespoons peanut butter in a small saucepan.
Pour into paper cup lined muffin tin, approximately 2 tablespoons.
Let cool.
Melt 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Pour over chocolate.
Cool.
Top with another tablespoon of chocolate peanut butter mixture.

title: buttermilk sugar cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and buttermilk with 2 teaspoons soda dissolved in it.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with mixer and chill thoroughly.
Drop on floured cookie sheet by tablespoonful. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° about 6 minutes.
Can be mixed by hand due to thickness of batter.
Makes approximately 8 dozen.

title: sweet summer corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease an 8.5 x 11-inch baking dish.

title: mexican lasagna with chicken
directions: Cook chicken and add the next 5 ingredients.
Then add 1/2 cup picante sauce and simmer.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese together. Spray lasagna pan with cooking spray.
Arrange 4 tortillas on bottom of pan.
Spread some of the chicken mixture over tortillas, then cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle green chilies; top with tablespoon sour cream over each tortilla, then spread some picante sauce and top with cheese.
Put next 4 tortillas and repeat layers.
Put remaining tortillas on top.
Put tablespoon sour cream on top of each tortilla; spread picante sauce on top, then add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and onion.
Brown chops.
Place chops in casserole.
Cover with potatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour soup over all.
This can be layered in a deep casserole.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cranberry pecan muffins
directions: Combine chopped cranberries and 1/4 cup sugar in small bowl; let stand.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and onion.
Mix with all other ingredients; put into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marshmallow fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and cocoa.
Cream with oleo. Add other ingredients, except marshmallows.
Cream well.
Grease and flour 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until done.
Sprinkle marshmallows and return to oven for 2 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all together and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: swiss tuna salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; chill until serving time.
Serve on lettuce or on buns; wrap in foil and heat for hot sandwich.

title: onion-cheese bread
directions: Cook onion in small amount of hot oil until tender but not browned.
Combine egg, milk and biscuit mix.
Add onion, half the cheese and parsley.
Spread dough in greased 8-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 1/2 minute.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes. Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: skillet corn and tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes and corn (including juices) in a large heavy skillet.
Add butter and oil and cook over medium heat until tender, stirring occasionally.
Season with pepper, salt, basil and nutmeg.
Stir in cheese and cook until melted.
Yields 6.

title: delicia
directions: Blend all ingredients; top with grated Colby cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrot, then fold in drained squash and onion.

title: tuna appetizer
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pack into greased 3 or 4 cup mold. Chill at least 4 hours.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: egg rolls
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots coarse.
Place in large microwave bowl.
Add sausage and cook 4 minutes.
Stir.
Add soy sauce, cornstarch, water and molasses.
Microwave until cabbage is wilted and sausage is done, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and microwave 2 minutes; let cool.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients until it's meal like.
Beat egg.
Add vinegar, brown sugar and water.
Add to flour and shortening mixture.
Mix all together.
Keep in a plastic bag in the refrigerator.
Keeps well for several weeks.
It doesn't make it tough to knead.
Makes 6 to 8 crusts.

title: savory cheese spread
directions: In bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, onion, green pepper and parsley.
In a blender container or food processor bowl, blend thoroughly Ricotta cheese, yogurt, catsup, mustard, hot pepper sauce and garlic salt.
Add the cheese mixture and blend until well combined (if using blender, you may have to mix in 2 batches).
Place in serving bowl and sprinkle with pimento and minced parsley.
Good served with crunch vegetables as a dip, over hot vegetables as a sauce or spread on slices of French bread and grill.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat with mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: au gratin vegetables
directions: Melt cheese in cream of mushroom soup.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Boil vegetables and put into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle onions on top.
Bake 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: chicken korma
directions: In a large kettle, saute onion and garlic in oil and butter. Add ginger, cardamom, cinnamon and salt.
Stir 1 minute.
Add chicken and brown.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Then cover and cook on low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add raisins and lemon juice.
Cook for 10 more minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: krugel
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Melt butter and pour in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients with noodles and pour in pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: poultry stuffings
directions: Melt 1/2 cup of the butter in a wide frying pan over medium heat.
Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden (about 15 minutes).
Add remaining 4 tablespoons butter, marjoram, pepper, sage and thyme.
Remove from heat.

title: orange muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, juice, rind and vanilla. Alternate mixture with buttermilk and flour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy-to-make cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place margarine in a loaf dish and put in oven to melt.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk.
Stir only until blended.
(Will be lumpy.)
Pour into dish and add fruit.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: olive pecan sandwiches
directions: Using food processor, chop pecans, olives and egg with enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Use as spread for crackers or on bread for sandwiches.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/2 cup water for 5 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Then add the broccoli.
Bake in a casserole dish for 30 minutes at 400°.
You may wish to crumble crackers and sprinkle on the top before baking.

title: raspberry snow bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream
Crisco,
salt
and 1/4 cup sugar until fluffy.
Blend in almond extract, egg yolks and mix in flour.
Pat dough into ungreased 13
x
9 x 2-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes, spread hot crust with preserves.
Top with coconut. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually	beat
in 1/2 cup sugar until stiff peaks form.
Spread over coconut.
Bake 25 minutes. Cool completely on rack, cut into 2 dozen squares.

title: italian chicken wings
directions: Discard tips of wings.
Cut remaining wing in 2 pieces.
Put chicken wings in bowl and cover with butter and mix around. Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and garlic powder in plastic bag.
Shake wings in crumb mixture.
Place chicken on greased 15 x 10-inch baking sheet and bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute; then add rest of ingredients.
Stir together; drop on wax paper with a tablespoon.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove yolks from halved eggs and mash together in bowl.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Scoop mixture into egg white halves by teaspoons.
Top with sliced stuffed green olives if desired.

title: macaroni-dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May let stand at least 8 hours. Freeze or bake right away.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° uncovered. Very easy to halve.
Serves 8.

title: easy stew
directions: Combine in crock-pot in morning; simmer all day.
Serve that night for dinner with rice, cornbread or biscuits.

title: wayne's famous strawberry cake
directions: Puree berries in a blender (add sugar to berries in blender). Combine all ingredients (except berries) in a large bowl and mix at a slow speed.
Mix in 3/4 of berry mix to batter at high speed. (Save remaining berry mix for frosting.)

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Heat together enchilada sauce, sour cream and soup.
Fill tortillas with meat, cheese and sauce, saving a portion of the sauce mixture and cheese for topping.
Roll up tortillas.
Place in 9x13x2 inch pan or dish. Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot dried beef spread
directions: Mix all together.
Spoon into 8-inch pie plate or small, shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve in hollowed out rye bread with pieces of bread and crackers.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Put in large container and shake to mix.
Mix 3 or 4 tablespoons of mix with 8 ounces of hot water.
Makes 72 servings.

title: amaretto pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together until smooth.
Add half the cocoa and half the Amaretto.
Mix well.
Add remaining cocoa, Amaretto and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, cover bottom pie shell with half the mixture.
Drizzle with 1/2 cup heated hot fudge topping.
Add rest of mixture.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream and shaved Hershey bar.
Can be prepared ahead.

title: shirt pocket
directions: Place cheese, meat and lettuce in pita pocket.
Pour dressing over top and serve.

title: co's special real italian spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large pot (10 quarts or larger) brown sausage links using medium heat.
Once all links are browned, add sauce, puree and whole tomatoes (cut up tomatoes as you add them to sauce).
Add chopped peppers, diced onions and sliced mushrooms.
Add all spices and stir.
Bring sauce to a boil with medium heat.
Reduce heat to simmer, cover sauce and cook on very low heat 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally to ensure sauce does not stick to bottom of pot.
Serve over pasta with Italian garlic bread and grated Parmesan cheese.
Can be used in any Italian or sauce dish. Great as pizza sauce, too.
Leftover sauce can be frozen up to 6 months.
Sauce taste gets better each time it's served.

title: the very best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat into submission the butter and sugars until light and creamy.
Add egg and beat it!
Now sift this: flour, salt and soda, then add to the creamy mixture.
Finally...add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop this mixture in teaspoons onto the cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Try to save one for somebody else.

title: the purple tulip
directions: Mix juices and sherbet in blender until smooth.
Pour into glasses and garnish with lemon slices.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Add peanut butter.
Add cornflakes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto foil.

title: bacon and onion cheesecake
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove to paper towels. Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of drippings. Cook onion and garlic in bacon drippings until tender, about 5 minutes. In a bowl, combine Ricotta, cream, flour, salt and pepper, blending until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time; blend until smooth. Stir in bacon, cooked onion mixture and green onions. Lightly grease a 9-inch spring-form pan. Pour batter into pan; bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is set. Cool on a wire rack. Serve at room temperature with assorted crackers.

title: chewy blond brownies
directions: Heat oven
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, beat together sugar and butter until well blended. Add remaining
ingredients;
mix
well.
Spread into prepared pan. Bake about 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: dee-lishus dump cake
directions: Oil a 9 x 13-inch baking liberally.
Layer pie filling and pineapple in baking pan.
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven or until dessert is golden brown. Yield: 10 servings.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per instructions.
Bake in 2 layers.
Mix marshmallows, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Cook until marshmallows are melted.
Stir in coconut; spread filling between cooled layers.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: grated apple dessert
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and margarine.
Beat well.
Add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: modified waldorf salad
directions: Core and dice apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add chopped up celery, pecans or walnuts and raisins.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice separately and fold into Cool Whip.
Spoon over apple mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Cover and chill. To serve, fold dressing into salad.

title: ground meat casserole(club member: nicholas)
directions: Brown meat in cooking oil; add onion, green pepper, olives, tomatoes and all seasonings. Add macaroni; pour into greased baking dish. Cover with grated cheese and bread crumbs. Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Serves 4.

title: chicken artichoke
directions: Wet breasts of chicken, then dip in flour.
Fry chicken in oil and garlic.
Add cooking wine last five minutes of frying.
Mix juice from frying pan with sour cream.
Put chicken, mushrooms, broccoli and artichoke hearts (cut in half and add all juice from can) in casserole dish.
Squeeze lemon on top if desired.
Break whole tomatoes and put on top (do not add juice).
Pour sour cream mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on last five minutes.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: chex party mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
On a cookie sheet, spread the mixture evenly.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Mixture should be turned every 15 minutes.
The mixture may also be placed in a metal bowl and stirred every 15 minutes for 45 minutes. Place on paper towels to absorb grease.

title: dilly ricotta muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and dill.
Combine milk, butter and eggs.
Stir in Ricotta and zucchini.
Add flour mixture.
Use muffin pans with liners.
Bake in 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: my great grandma's butter bean soup
directions: Cook about 2 hours or until tender.

title: new orleans chicken
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients in a shallow dish, mixing well.
Roll chicken in flour to coat, then dip into sauce.
Place chicken in single layer in lightly greased pan.
Cover; bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 300°; continue baking for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add flour and cinnamon gradually. Add other ingredients.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: mccall's microwave chocolate-drizzled peanut butter fudge
directions: Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Place sugar, milk and butter in a microwave-safe 3-quart casserole with straight sides. Microwave on High 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes more, or until small amount of sugar mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in ice water, or until mixture reaches 236° on candy thermometer.
(Do not leave candy thermometer in microwave.)

title: four flavor freeze
directions: Combine cookie crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter; press into refrigerator tray.
Chill.
Break ice cream into chunks; beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Fold in bananas and nuts; pour into crumb crust.
Freeze until firm.
Fold remaining sugar into whipped cream.
Spread on ice cream.
Sprinkle chocolate over whipped cream and freeze.
Place tray on warm damp cloth for a few minutes to loosen crust before serving.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in double boiler.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, marshmallows, egg and nuts.
Divide mixture in two parts and roll.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap well and refrigerate.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: garlic string beans
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, heat the oil.
Add garlic and beans. Saute over high heat to sear beans, stirring frequently so they do not burn.
Add thyme, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil. Cover tightly.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until beans are tender when pierced with tip of sharp knife. Add more water, if necessary.
Frozen beans will take only half the time. Add squeeze of lemon juice and toss well. Serves 2.

title: vegetable hors d'oeuvres
directions: Flatten crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix; chill. Spread chilled mixture on cooled crust.
Press vegetables (except tomatoes) on top.
Chill 2 hours or longer.
Before serving, place tomatoes and cheese on top.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Melt cheese with Ro-Tel.
Mix chicken and soup.
Layer Doritos in greased casserole dish.
Pour chicken mixture on Doritos.
Pour Ro-Tel and cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix
margarine,
sugar	and
eggs
well.
Sift together flour, baking
powder
and salt.
Chill for 1 hour.
Form into balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixed together.	Place on greased cookie
sheet.
Bake until light golden brown at 400° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: simple rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water until tender.
Add margarine, sugar and raisins.
Take off heat.
Add well-beaten eggs, vanilla and milk. Stir well.
Bake in casserole dish in 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Mix ingredients together, spread on cookie sheet.
Spread with chocolate frosting and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in small saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Beat eggs with fork in small bowl. Stir in corn syrup, sugar and vanilla;
pour this mixture into saucepan and mix
well
with chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until filling is set.
It should be	firm
on top but soft inside.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: quick enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef with seasonings and onion.
Drain.
Place sauce in a bowl wide enough to dip tortillas in.
Put about 1/4-inch of oil in frypan.
Heat oil.
Put 3 tablespoons of sauce in a cake pan or a large casserole dish.
Spread until bottom of pan is covered in sauce.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine and spoon over chicken mixture.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in casserole dish.
Mix with soup and milk.
Cover with chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer in order given. Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in tight container.
To serve, mix 4 tablespoons mix in mug.
Fill with boiling water.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish, 9 x 12-inch.
Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix on bottom.
Add mixture.
Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Take from bones and cut into small pieces.
Mix 2 cups of broth with soup and bring to a boil.
In separate bowl, mix butter, pepper, salt, flour and buttermilk. Lay chicken in baking dish.
Pour broth mixture over top of chicken, then spread dough mixture over top.
Bake 25 minute on 400°.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except peaches.
Lay peaches on top of pie shell.
Cover with cream mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Pie should be firm; if not, bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: beer 'n sausage
directions: Place beer, onion, carrot, Worcestershire sauce and salt in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add bratwursts.
Cover and simmer 15 more minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place bratwursts in buns.
With a slotted spoon, lift vegetables from liquid and place on brats.
Serves 8.

title: banana cookies(diabetic)
directions: Combine bananas, oil and vanilla.
Stir in oats, walnuts and raisins.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Press down with fork and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin - walnut - raisin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix well.
In separate bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour batter into two greased bread loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Pour into an empty 9-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: garden salad bowl
directions: Cook vegetables separately until barely tender.
Cool. Combine oil, cheeses, vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and oregano in a jar.
Cover and shake well before pouring over vegetables.
Toss in green onions.
Chill overnight.

title: cherry parfait pie
directions: Beat first five ingredients in small mixer bowl at high speed until
smooth.
Combine
water and gelatin, let stand 1 minute. Place
over
simmering water until gelatin dissolves. Beat gelatin mixture
into
cream cheese mixture until smooth. Blend in sour cream.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon 1 cup of the cherry pie filling
into
the graham cracker crust and top with the cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until set (approximately 4 hours). Top
with
the remaining cherry pie filling and garnish with additional whipped topping.

title: okra soup(charleston)
directions: Cook meat in water for 2 hours in a
large pot.
Add tomatoes, okra, onion, butter beans, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 more hour at low heat, adding water if needed. Stir, season to taste and let simmer 15 minutes.
Serve hot with cornbread.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together 4 times.
Cream the shortening.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Add figs; blend well.
Bake in well-greased layer cake pans (3) at 350°.
Test for doneness at 35 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat milk and cheese together until cheese melts and butter. Beat eggs in casserole and add other ingredients.
Cook at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: cajun pinto beans
directions: Cook beans by package directions.
Cook both sausages on stovetop over medium heat.
Cut smoked sausage into bite size pieces before cooking.
Drain grease and rinse with hot water. Add sausages to beans and seasoning.
Cook for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients first.
Add remaining ingredients and mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 4 small or 2 large loaves.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix yeast in water to dissolve.
Mix all ingredients together; blend well with a spoon.
Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes, then spoon into muffin tins and bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: risotto primavera
directions: Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil.
Add peas, pepper, garlic and asparagus; saute until tender.
Season with salt and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Saute shallot.
Add rice; cook until golden.
Add heated chicken broth; cook until tender.
Mix together with vegetable mixture.
Add half and half and cheese. Salt and pepper, if desired.
Serve.

title: sausage cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Add the sugar to the sausage and mix well.
Add the eggs and mix well.
Mix flour, spices and baking powder.
Stir baking soda into coffee.
Add flour mixture and coffee alternately to meat mixture, beating well after each addition.
Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain and dry on paper towel.
Fold raisins and nuts into batter.
Pour into pan and bake for 90 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Place flour, margarine and 1/2 cup nuts into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish to make crust. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes. Set aside to cool.

title: braised carrots
directions: Scrape and slice carrots.
Cook until tender; drain and cool. Mix other ingredients in larger bowl and pour over carrots. Refrigerate 12 hours.
(Keeps well in refrigerator.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish, potatoes, onion and slices of margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat layers until dish is full (1 inch from top of dish).
Pour evaporated milk over casserole.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Pour grated cheese over casserole and return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook until no longer pink.
Add Pasta Accents and salsa; stir to combine.
Cover and reduce heat to medium.
Simmer 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve with additional salsa and sour cream, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: applesauce jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add applesauce and lemon juice. Pour into mold and chill.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine ham, beef, eggs, crumbs and seasonings.
Mix by hand and form into balls.
Place in pans.
Combine soup, brown sugar and vinegar.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender; cut/shred into bite size pieces.
Mix onion, chiles, soups, water/broth and garlic together with chicken in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; then remove from heat. Cut tortillas into 1 inch pie shaped pieces.
Layer tortillas, chicken soup mixture and cheese alternately in a large casserole; continue with layers ending with cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven uncovered.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: mrs. glover's summer soup
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in a large pan.
Add enough water to make soup consistency.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add corn oil and salt and or sugar to taste.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix together and pat in 9-inch spring-form pan.
Save some for top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: john's burritos
directions: Trim round steak, removing all the fat.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips, lengthwise, and then cut into 1/2-inch pieces, crosswise.

title: marinara sauce(no fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, at least 2 hours.
Cool to room temperature and refrigerate or freeze.
Store in plastic bags in freezer.
Pop bag in microwave and serve it over pasta or rice or use it as a sauce for fish, poultry or meat. Can also be used for a soup or base for a spicy stew.

title: aeppler apple-date torte
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to egg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in 8 x 12 x 2-inch greased pan.
When cooled, cut into squares and top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: golden punch
directions: In a small pot, bring to a boil enough water to dissolve sugar.
Pour dissolved sugar into a 2 1/2-gallon container.
Add pineapple juice, water, orange juice, lemonade and water.
Add citric acid and stir well.
Add additional sugar to taste.
If you have enough notice, freeze.

title: pudding fruit salad
directions: Combine pudding and whipped cream.
Mix well; add fruit.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease well a 10-inch pie plate, glass preferably.
Spread cranberries over bottom.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and nuts. Beat eggs well.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually and beat until smooth. Add flour, melted margarine and shortening; beat well.
Pour over top of berries.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: fried pumpkin
directions: Peel and cube pumpkin and cook until tender.
Add to pumpkin the water, sugar, salt and butter.
Cook slow for about 20 to 30 minutes.
May add cinnamon or allspice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line 2 unbaked pie shells with pecans.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon fizz(diabetic recipe)
directions: Crush ice cubes; divide between 2 (10-ounce) glasses. Dissolve sweetener in lemon juice, then pour 2 1/2 tablespoons of mixture on top of crushed ice.
Pour half bottle club soda into each glass; stir briskly.
Cut lemon slices halfway through to core; garnish side of each glass with a lemon slice.

title: pizza soup
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion, pepper, garlic powder and oregano over medium-high heat, stirring frequently, 3 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes (longer is even better).
Sprinkle with cheese before serving.
I serve this soup with fresh baked breadsticks.
Makes 7 (1/2-cup) servings, 99 calories, 6 g. fat, 604 mg. sodium, 11 mg. cholesterol.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add milk and corn, pour into a casserole dish, about 2-inches deep.
Pour melted butter on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls.
Coat in additional powdered sugar.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Partially thaw frozen bread.
Slice each loaf into 7 or 8 equal sections.
Allow to completely thaw.
Roll each piece out, then place pepperoni slices over surface; cover with cheese.
Roll and place on lightly greased cookie sheet, seam side down.

title: easy tortellini soup
directions: Cook the tortellini in chicken broth.
Add minestrone soup and chunky tomatoes. Cook sausage; drain fat and add to soup.
Simmer. Add cheese, if desired.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cut the bacon into 1/2-inch pieces and lay in bottom of a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake in microwave 3 to 4 minutes.
Add the potatoes and onion; cover with the clam juice from the canned clams.
Cook in the microwave 10 to 15 minutes, until the potatoes are tender.
Add 1 2/3 cups milk (I use part half and half and part milk).
Mix the remaining 1/3 cup milk with the flour.
Add to potato mixture and stir.
Cook in the microwave for 8 to 10 minutes, until thickened; stir every 2 minutes.
When the mixture is thickened, add the clams and whipping cream.
Cook another 4 minutes.

title: belinda's "fast" fixin remoulade sauce
directions: Whip it all together.
Use it over shrimp salad.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spiced orange mold
directions: Drain liquid from oranges into small pan.
Add sugar, water and spices.
Boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Place jello into bowl and pour hot liquid through strainer into jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add fruit, orange juice and lemon juice.
Spoon into molds.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Put in pie shell and refrigerate for 2 hours or more.

title: black walnut sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add water and continue to beat.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add vanilla, cinnamon, salt, nuts and flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: seafood bisque(serves 4)
directions: Puree seafood with 1 cup stock in blender or processor.
Boil rice in remaining stock and wine until tender; puree and add to seafood.
Saute vegetables in oil until tender; puree and add to seafood.
Add cream to combined mixture; season with salt and pepper.
Simmer gently about 5 minutes.
Pass through sieve if texture is not completely smooth.
Thin with more stock if mixture is too thick.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Make cream sauce of ingredients.
Place cabbage in casserole. Pour sauce over, then sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in oven until crumbs are browned in about 350° oven.

title: holiday strudel
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, pineapple juice, flour, salt and baking powder. This forms the dough. Roll out the dough in a large square. Spread one side of dough with strawberry preserves. Spread the other side with peach preserves. On the whole square, sprinkle sour cherries, crushed pineapple, maraschino cherries, raisins, nuts, cinnamon and sugar. Fold dough carefully in a roll and place on greased cookie sheet. To give glossy top, beat egg and brush over top. Sprinkle cinnamon sugar over top of roll. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: pauline's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg and oil and cream.
Mix in flour, salt and baking soda.
Roll into balls the size of a marble.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press down with fingers.
Bake at 300°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as detailed on the box.
Add Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Crush cookies with food processor or blender.
Add layers of the cream cheese mixture, then cookies, until cream cheese mixture is gone.
Make sure cookies are last layer, then refrigerate.

title: french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, beat together eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Dip bread in egg mixture, coating both sides.
In a skillet, cook bread on both sides in a small amount of hot butter or oil over medium-high heat until golden brown. Add more butter if needed.
Cover with syrup or honey.

title: mom's shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill.
Serve with crackers as appetizer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer in baking dish, 1 or 2 layers as desired.
End with layer of cheese.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lorna's meat pie
directions: Combine and mix well.
Pat mixture into a greased fluted pie pan (9 or 10-inch).

title: copper or penny carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots until tender.
Cool and alternate layers of carrots, peppers and onions.
Mix tomato soup, salad oil, sugar, 3/4 cup vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire.
Pour over carrots.
Serve right away or marinate overnight.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs
well;
add
sugar.
Let milk get hot but not boil. Pour into egg and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 300° until light brown.

title: pralines
directions: Put 1/4 cup sugar in iron skillet, cook until dark, don't let it burn. Meanwhile in a heavy pot, mix 2 cups sugar and milk. When it comes to a boil, add the cooked sugar from the skillet, stirring constantly. Cook to soft boil stage. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Beat until mixture thickens and loses shine. Quickly drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Arrange pecans on top.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, mixing well after each addition.
Chill several hours or overnight.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness; cut with 3-inch round cookie cutter.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. While stirring with a wire whisk, add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
In pretty glass serving bowl, layer pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas, ending with pudding.
Cover; chill.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well.
Add nuts, raisins, dates and apples.
Oil and flour an angel food pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Please note:
This cake is delicious just with apples. Nuts, raisins and dates are optional.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease a 9-inch baking pan.
Beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Add a little sugar to proof the yeast.
Heat the milk and shortening just until shortening is melted.
Do not boil.
In a large mixing bowl, measure the sugar, salt and 1 cup flour.
Pour in the heated mixture and beat with a hand beater until thoroughly mixed.
Add the yeast, after checking the temperature of the mixture in the bowl.
Not too hot or it will "kill" the yeast.
Add another cup of flour and continue to beat with the beater.
Add the egg now, if you desire.
Take out beaters and mix in enough more flour so dough is not sticky.
Push dough down into bowl.
Cover and let rest for about 15 minutes.
Prepare a floured breadboard and push dough onto it.
Knead flour into dough until it is easy to handle.
Then continue kneading for about 10 minutes.
Grease bowl and put smoothed dough in to rise.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and make into two loaves and a 9 x 9-inch pan of biscuits.
Cover with a towel and let rise again until doubled in volume.
Bake in a 400° preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes until crust is a golden brown. Turn onto cooling racks.
Butter the top of loaves and biscuits. Serve to the hurrahs of your family.
Great warm with peanut butter and homemade strawberry jam.

title: cucumber breads
directions: Mix cream cheese and Italian salad dressing.
Spread over slices of rye bread.
Sprinkle dry dill on top of cucumber slices.

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Bake cake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes as directed on package in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Poke holes in the cake as soon as it comes from the oven.
Pour sweetened condensed milk in the holes, then pour ice cream topping over the milk.
Cool completely.
Frost with Cool Whip. Crush the candy bars and sprinkle over the top. Refrigerate.

title: date pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Cream well.
Add beaten egg whites. Fold in dates and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and cabbage casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 10-inch skillet; add potato.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add cabbage. Cook over medium heat until cabbage is crisp-tender.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add sausage, cheese and mustard.
Heat until hot.

title: chocolate covered creams
directions: Mix all ingredients except the paraffin wax and chocolate chips. Roll into small balls and chill. Melt the semi-sweet chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler. Stick toothpick in candy ball and dip in mixture. Place on wax paper.

title: banana boat
directions: Have Granny slice large banana lengthwise and spread mayonnaise on flat side of banana.
Then have Granny smash some peanuts. Child can have good time sprinkling crushed peanuts on top of mayonnaise.
Granny can have a half and child can have half.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon.
Flake salmon and add remaining ingredients, combining well.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Clean knife test for doneness.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour over flour in 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Press flour down to bottom of pan to form crust.
Bake at 350° until brown.
When crust has cooked, soften cream cheese and beat with powdered sugar and 4 tablespoons Cool Whip until creamy. Spread over crust.
Beat instant pudding with milk until thick. Pour into pan and spread.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Decorate with Nestle semi-sweet mini morsels.
Refrigerate until served.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt the peanut butter and margarine together.
Add the confectioners sugar.
Mash the mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt the Hershey's chocolate and pour over the top. Let cool; cut into squares.

title: caramel
directions: Mix everything together in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until hard ball stage (approximately 245°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add nuts, if used.
Pour hot liquid into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool in pan until bottom is not hot to the touch.
Turn out on a marble slab or lightly buttered surface.
Cut into cubes and wrap in wax paper or cut into cubes and dip in chocolate.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Chill before rolling.
Roll and cut with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in 450° oven.
Let cookies stay in 450° oven 1 minute and turn turn oven to 375°.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Nutmeg may be used instead of vanilla (about 1/2 teaspoon full).

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello, marshmallows and cream cheese in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Drain pineapple and use juice combined with ice water to make 1 cup.
Stir into hot gelatin mixture.
Let set until syrupy.
Add pineapple, carrots and almonds.
Pour into mold to set.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm in the middle.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes (35 for glass pan).

title: spiced shrimp kebabs
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/4 cup syrup.
In skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Saute garlic, spices and tomato paste 2 minutes.
Add shrimp; saute 2 minutes.
Stir in pineapple syrup and remaining ingredients; boil.
Add pineapple; place in bowl. Accompany with picks to make kebabs.
Yields 4 servings, 139 calories per serving.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Add cheese, Rice Krispies and salt. Mix well with hands as heat helps melt cheese.
Roll into balls and flatten with a small glass.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: fruit and cream
directions: First Layer:
Combine margarine and graham cracker crumbs; spread out in square pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Now refrigerate to cool while mixing the second layer.

title: basic tomato sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in a large saucepan.
Add onions and garlic. Saute over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove and discard garlic.
Add tomatoes, basil, oregano, salt, pepper, tomato paste and sugar.
Heat to boiling, then simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes or until thickened.

title: pork chops 'n rice
directions: Brown both sides of chops in skillet.
Season to taste.
Drain fat.
Place rice in rectangular baking dish, 12 x 8-inch, etc. Pour orange juice over rice.
Pour chicken soup over this; cover. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes or until done.

title: roasted mustard potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a roasting pan 3 times with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Prick potatoes several times with the tines of a fork.

title: spaghetti with tuna sauce
directions: In skillet, saute garlic with all the olive oil over medium heat. Add parsley and cook for 1/2 minute. Add tomatoes. Stir well.
Lower heat and cook at a gentle simmer for 25 minutes or until tomatoes separate from oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix in the drained tuna.
Mix well and cook for 5 minutes. Add butter and serve over pasta.

title: marinated grilled sirloin tips
directions: Mix all ingredients in large sealable bag.
Shake well.
Add sirloin tips.
Marinate at least 4 hours, overnight is better! Then grill to preference.

title: baked rhubarb
directions: Dice the rhubarb, but do not peel.
Place with the sugar & spices and the juice, pulp, and grated rind of the orange in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven (350°) about 45 minutes, or until tender.
If desired, the cover may be removed during the last 15 minutes of cooking.
Serves 6.

title: ziti casserole
directions: Cook the pasta as directed; reduce cooking time to 5 minutes. Saute beef until well browned.
Add mushrooms and garlic and cook 3 minutes.
Drain ziti.
Combine meat mixture, sauce, wine, oregano, salt and pepper.
Add ziti and mix.
Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9-inch baking dishes and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: orange salad
directions: Cook pudding, jello and water until it comes to a boil.
Let cool. Add diced oranges to mixture. Mix in Cool Whip and chill. Serves 12 to 15.

title: texas cole slaw
directions: Mix together dressing.
Mix salad and noodles together and just before serving, toss thoroughly with dressing.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In mixer, blend eggs, sugar, salt, mustard and honey until thickened.
Slowly add oil and vinegar.
Stir in poppy seed and onion.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: sweet party mix
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Add pecans and stir. Add cereal and stir.
Place in baking dish sprayed with Pam and bake at 325° for 7 minutes.
Stir and bake another 7 minutes. Cool completely and store in airtight container.

title: autumn fruit cake
directions: Line bottom of tube pan with a round of greased paper or foil and cut a straight strip for the sides.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients with nuts last.

title: hawaiian delight cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle 4 tablespoons graham cracker crumbs on the bottom of a 9-inch round pan.
Soften gelatin in water.
Drain pineapple, reserve juice and add water to make 3/4 cup.
Bring to a boil and dissolve softened gelatin.
Beat cottage cheese in blender and add egg yolks, milk, lemon juice, sweetener and vanilla.
Blend in gelatin.
Chill until thick, but not set.
Beat egg whites, gently fold into gelatin mixture.
Spoon over crumbs in pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over filling.
Top with pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Takes about 4 hours.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Pour salt over slices.
Top with ice.
Let soak for 3 hours. Add spices, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Let mixture come to a boil.
Pack in jars.

title: elliott's vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Grind vegetables in food processor.
Squeeze juice through colander, paper towels or whatever works best for you.
Save 6 tablespoons of juice aside.
Barely heat juice to dissolve gelatine.
Let cool.
After cool, add to vegetables.
Add the mayonnaise.
Mix and chill.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring butter and cocoa to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour onto a large lightly greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Frost with Texas Sheet Cake Frosting.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Pour all the ingredients into a baked pie shell and chill.

title: easy summer salad
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
To make salad for a large group, increase oil, sugar and vinegar always to equal amounts and add more vegetables.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, molasses, salt, soda and spices. Add flour.
Place teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten a wee bit with fork dipped in cold water. Sprinkle generously with white sugar.
Bake in preheated 375° oven about 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Store in Ziploc freezer bags (quart size).

title: company cauliflower
directions: Brown mushrooms and pepper lightly in butter.
Add flour and milk to make sauce.
Add salt.
Arrange a layer of cooked cauliflower in a casserole dish, cover with cheese slices and then sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese slices. Add paprika. Brown lightly in a 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Very Good!!!

title: gold and white wedding cake
directions: Line the bottom of each cake pan with waxed paper.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Sift flour with baking powder and add to creamed mixture a little at a time, alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with flour. Fill cake pans about half full with batter.
This makes a very high cake.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes (test before, depending on pan used, will determine time).
Makes 3 (8 or 9-inch) layers or 1 (13 x 9-inch) rectangle.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda, salt, ginger and cloves.
Mix in nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken shish kabob
directions: Simmer all ingredients except chicken and vegetables for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Cube the chicken breasts and marinate in sauce for at least 1 hour.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well with a spoon or spatula.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x2-inch glass dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: black-eyed peas casserole
directions: Prepare ahead: green pepper and onion.
Cook sausage in a large frying pan, crumbling with fork as it cooks.
Drain off fat. Add vegetables to sausage.
Cook about 5 minutes on medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add tomatoes and seasoning.
Stir well.
Add black-eyed peas, including liquid. Cover and simmer slowly, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve very hot with grated cheese sprinkled on top.
Can be prepared ahead and reheated.
Do not add cheese until ready to serve.

title: vietnam cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.
These cookies are so named because we mailed them to the GI's in Vietnam during the 1960's.

title: cheese dip
directions: Whip ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Serve in a hollowed out round loaf of bread.
Use bread cubes for dipping.

title: strawberry poke cake
directions: You will need two round pans (8 or 9 x 1/2-inch).
Do not use pans with removable bottoms.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add soda to milk; add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add nuts, vanilla and bananas.
Bake in well greased tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter together (on top of stove or in microwave).
Pour over cereal and stir until coated.
Put powdered sugar in plastic bag suitable for food storage; pour in cereal mixture and shake well.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Chop the tomato and onion.
Mince the peppers and garlic. Combine all ingredients and let stand for at least 1 hour.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: chicken bites
directions: Cover 2 baking sheets with aluminum foil.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix cracker crumbs, cheese, seasoned salt, thyme, basil and pepper.
Heat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken pieces into melted butter, then into crumb mixture.
Place chicken pieces about 1/2-inch apart on baking sheets.
Bake uncovered until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir by hand.
Do not beat.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Let cool slightly before putting on cake plate.
Then dust lightly with powdered sugar.

title: braised beef and noodles
directions: Salt, pepper and flour stew beef.
Brown in small amount of oil. Add onion, garlic and celery. Cook until clear.
Add soup and stir. Add tomato puree and stir. Add water.
Add bay leaves, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Let cook 1 1/2 hours. Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Makes 6 generous servings. Sauce freezes well.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole dish.
Crush 35 Ritz crackers and spread over vegetables.
Melt 3/4 stick butter and pour over crackers.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit bowl cake
directions: Take half of cake; break into pieces and put in large bowl. Spread half of the pudding over cake, pineapple over pudding and 1 container of Cool Whip over the pineapple.
Break other half of cake into pieces over the Cool Whip.
Spread rest of pudding over cakes, peaches over pudding, Mandarin oranges over peaches and other container Cool Whip over peaches.
Top with coconut, if desired.

title: chicken fantastic
directions: Mix
onion soup mix, apricot jam
and
French
dressing, stirring thoroughly with wire whisk.
Dip
chicken into mixture and allow to marinate 3 hours in refrigerator.
Place in baking dish and pour rest of marinade over all.
Bake
in 350° oven 40 to 50 minutes.
Turn once and bake additional
minutes
at 400°. Serve with rice.
(If you use boned and skinned breasts, lower the baking time to 35 minutes.)

title: summer strawberry surprise
directions: Melt the 3 sticks of butter on medium heat, stirring often until it boils.
While it is still bubbly, add the flour and 5 Tbsp. sugar -- keep stirring and cook for 3 more minutes.
Let this mixture cool for a few minutes then spread onto an oblong cookie sheet.
Pat down and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Let it completely cool.
In the meantime, cream the powdered sugar and cream cheese; add vanilla.
Fold in 3 cups of the Cool Whip. Spread on the cooled crust.
Slice the strawberries; add a little sugar to sweeten the berries, and fold into the remaining Cool Whip.
Spread on top of the creamed sugar/cream cheese mixture.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip.
After well mixed, fold in Cool Whip.

title: marinated zucchini salad
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients, mix well and set aside.
Slice zucchini and artichoke hearts into a large bowl.
Add remaining vegetables; add dressing mixture, stir until vegetables are coated.
Cover; chill overnight.
This will keep for 1 week in the refrigerator.
The longer it marinates, the better it gets.

title: mother's pecan pie
directions: Put pecans in pie shell.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over pecans.
Bake at 325° until nuts are crisp.

title: raspberry refresher
directions: Make pina colada as directed.
Blend in raspberries.
Serve cold.

title: patience cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Bake two round layers.
With thread, cut each layer into four layers.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour plenty on top of each layer.
Put in freezer for two days.

title: spaghetti dinner
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Brown hamburg, then add spaghetti sauce and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Spray pan with Pam.
Mix egg and milk together and put spaghetti into it and mix.
Pour into pan.
Add meat and sauce.
Add pepperoni and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla into blender; process on low until sugar is dissolved and eggs are lemon colored.
Add milk; process until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: my chicken salad(lo-cal - good)
directions: Combine ingredients with Weight Watchers dressing.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Mix jello with boiling water to dissolve.
Mix with Kool-Aid.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice and half of 7-Up.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, add rest of 7-Up.

title: portuguese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skin until tender; cut into bite size pieces.
Place potatoes in large, flat casserole dish.
Mix parsley, paprika and garlic salt together.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Mix pimentos, onion and cubed cheese.
Place over potatoes.
Top cheese with bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter over entire casserole.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 15 minutes or until bubbly; do not overbake.

title: festive cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water. Add the cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple with juice; mix well. Congeal. Add 1/2 cup nuts, if desired. (Can use sugar-free Jell-O).

title: strawberry icebox jello pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, then fold in ice cream and frozen strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Top with whipped cream when served.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Toss cheeses together.
Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients except Doritos chips and cheese.
Layer in order 1/2 Doritos chips, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheeses; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: road kill chili
directions: Cooking Chili Meat:
(Note: Meat should not be green and all rocks and other road debris should be removed.)
Heat oil and cook onions and meat until meat is browned.
Add all spices and mix well.
Add the tomatoes (including juice), tomato paste and water; bring to a boil.
Cook, partly covered, stirring frequently, for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When ready to serve, stir in beans and serve piping hot.

title: candy apple pie
directions: In large bowl, toss together apples, walnuts, candies, 1/3 cup sugar and flour.
Pour into pie crusts.
Break or crumble 2nd frozen pie crust into very small pieces.
Toss with remaining 2 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.

title: carrots and white grapes
directions: Cook carrots; do not overcook.
Drain.
Melt butter; add liqueur and grapes.
Pour over carrots just before you serve.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend butter and cheese.
Mix in flour, paprika and salt. Wrap 1 teaspoon dough around each olive, completely covering it. Wrap in foil.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, unwrap desired number; put on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes (less if fresh) or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: midnight pie
directions: Mix together the butter and flour.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press the pecans into the crust.
Bake in
a 350° oven for 10 minutes. Let crust completely cool.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; toss lightly.
Serve immediately.

title: green beans with mushroom-onion topping
directions: Prepare the beans for cooking.
Peel and slice the onions. Boil or steam the beans and onions for about 7 minutes in salted water. Drain. Reserve cooking liquid for soup or sauce.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit.
Mix into bowl with bananas.
Mix in cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: amber's biscuits
directions: Pour mixture on floured cutting board and roll dough out smooth, then cut out biscuits.
Let cook 20 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberries 'n sour cream pancakes
directions: Combine milk, eggs, flour and salt; beat until smooth.
Heat heavy, ovenproof 9-inch skillet in 450° oven until very hot.
Add butter to coat skillet; pour batter in immediately.
Bake on lowest rack in oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue cooking for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Fill with combined sour cream and sugar.
Top with strawberries.
Cut into wedges and serve immediately

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese and garlic salt; add mayonnaise and artichokes and mix well.
Place in a casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs (example: Ritz or Club crackers), and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake 1/2 batch at 350° for 15 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Serve on your favorite crackers.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix.
Spread on shallow dish (8 to 10-inches round).
Refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: sophisticated chicken
directions: Put slices of dried beef on top of breast and roll.
Do this for all breast portions.
Wrap each piece with a slice of bacon to hold together.
Cover bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish with dried beef.
Arrange chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over all.
Sprinkle seasoning salt on top.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours (uncovered).
Serves 8.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put chops in bottom of baking dish.
Place rice over chops. Slice onion and green pepper over rice.
Pour water and tomatoes over onion and green pepper.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: van's cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients with eggs.
Add milk until batter is cake batter consistency.
Pour into greased iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: date and orange muffins
directions: Cut orange into pieces, remove seeds and drop pieces into blender.
Blend until rind is finely ground.
Add juice, dates, egg and butter and give another whirl in blender.
Sift remaining ingredients into a bowl.
Pour orange mixture over them and stir lightly.
Drop spoonfuls into 18 buttered muffin tins and bake in 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
These muffins freeze well but should be used within 8 weeks.

title: southern pepper steak
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil; saute onion and pepper until tender.
Remove from oil.
Cut steak into thin slices, roll in flour, salt and pepper and brown in oil until done.
Remove steak to drain.
Discard oil.

title: cookie cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: no-flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put half pecan on top and press down.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This recipe contains no flour.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry). Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder on bottom of 13 x 9 baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Mix together, place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt, margarine and milk in heavy saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Mix well. Add raisins at this time, if desired in cookies. Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet or waxed paper. Cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thick and then cool completely. Mix rest of ingredients together and pour dressing over, mixing well.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix with mixer, eggs, sugar and melted butter or margarine. When well blended add pineapple, juice, coconut and corn meal. Blend well.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: low-fat mexican chicken and rice
directions: Pour picante sauce into Pyrex dish and place chicken in the sauce.
Turn chicken over and bake for about 35 or 40 minutes. Turn chicken over again and cover with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake for another 15 or 20 minutes.
Cheese will melt and mix with picante sauce for a gravy-like mixture.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix separately the remaining ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Pour it into 6 small loaf pans sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 6 small loaves.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook beef, onions and garlic over medium heat until meat is slightly browned.
Stir in tomato sauce, milk, eggs, corn, etc. Place into 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes clean.
Pierce with fork and microwave potatoes for about 8 minutes or until tender to the squeeze.
Cut hot potatoes in half, the long ways.
Scoop out all but 1/4-inch of the meat of the potato (meat may be saved and used for mashed potatoes).
Place potato halves in oven-safe casserole dish. Carefully put oil in each potato half.
Season with salt to taste. Bake in preheated 350° oven and fill each half with bacon, then top with cheese and bake for 10 minutes.
If desired, top with sour cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in boiler and saute onions. Add the broccoli, cream of chicken soup, rice and water. Stir together and heat through. Stir in cheese. Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Mix together and drop rounded teaspoonful of dough about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400° until delicately browned on edges. Frost with icing below.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; add enough water to the juice to make 1 cup. In large saucepan, blend liquid with the cornstarch.
Simmer gently, stirring frequently.
Add vinegar, soy sauce, brown sugar and spice.
Add pieces of cooked chicken and pineapple; simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Stir-fried or steamed vegetables make a good side dish.

title: quick chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: golden ham casserole
directions: Fry mushrooms, onions and butter for 5 minutes.
Remove mushrooms.
Add flour and seasonings to butter and blend. Gradually add milk while stirring and cook until thickened.
Add cheese; blend.
Stir in ham and mushrooms.
Turn into buttered casserole and top with bread.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add pecans, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Chill for one hour covered.
Roll into about 2 inch balls. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for one to two minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix sugars, eggs, vanilla, syrup and baking soda.
Add butter and peanut butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until just turning brown, or about 10 minutes.

title: pork casserole
directions: Brown meat and pork in large Dutch oven kettle. Add celery and mushrooms. Add mushrooms, soup, salt and pepper. Cover and put in oven. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Take out and add chow mein noodles, mixing in juice lightly. Do not cover. Put back in oven approximately 5 to 7 minutes. Serve.

title: party salad
directions: Add jello to cottage cheese; blend.
Add fruit and then fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 4 hours.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix cherries, chopped dates, coconut and pecans together making sure it is mixed well.
Add the flour, baking powder and vanilla. Add condensed milk.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: tyler's pink cookies
directions: Crush peppermint candy extra fine.
Melt chocolate and mix with crushed candy.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper and let cool until firm.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Heat strawberries to a boil.
Pour strawberry jello in and stir until jello is mixed.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip. Mix with mixer until smooth.
Chil until firm.
Serve.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans.
Spread and press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool.
Combine the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip; blend thoroughly.
Spread over cooled baked crust.
Chill. Combine pudding mix and milk; continue beating until pudding has thickened.
Spread pudding over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Refrigerate.

title: tri-cheese noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles until tender and drain well.
Cut butter and cheese into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients (except corn flakes) to hot noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 3-quart oblong Pyrex casserole.
Top with crumbled corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add milk, vanilla and coconut. Add cut up fruit that has been soaking in 1/2 cup whiskey.
Add cut up nuts.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to fruit mixture and mix by hand with wooden spoon until all is blended well.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours in 4 aluminum bread pans that have been lined with wax paper.
Good luck.

title: easy vinaigrette
directions: Spoon mustard into bowl and whisk in vinegar, sugar, pepper and herbs.
Slowly dribble oil into mustard mixture, whisking continuously.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Vinaigrette is best if made just before serving.
Serve over salads or steamed vegetables.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix with hands.
Roll out in walnut-sized balls.
Make thumbprint in center.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Fill with powdered sugar icing.

title: almond cookies
directions: Mix lard and sugar until creamy.
Add flour and baking soda. Add vanilla, almond flavoring and beaten eggs (add eggs last).

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls about the size of hickory nuts.
Let stand for a while, then roll in powdered sugar. Store in airtight container.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, and milk; bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Really watch this, it scorches easy.
After the 5 minutes of boiling, remove from heat and add chocolate morsels, stir until blended. Add marshmallow cream nuts and vanilla, stir vigorously until all is mixed well.
Pour mixture out onto a large surface, (I use a heavy big glass tray that has been buttered).
Spread out fudge and add some of the mini marshmallows and some of the extra nuts in the middle of the fudge.
Now fold both sided into the middle with a wide pastry knife.
Spread out again and add more marshmallows and nuts as desired, being sure to continue folding the fudge.
When desired mixture is reached, smooth out fudge and allow to cool. Cut into squares, or into loafs for gifts.
You can garnish top of fudge with pecan halves, or sugar seasonal decoration (Wilton Products).

title: pecan rolls
directions: In saucepan, add butter, water, brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Cook to a boil.
Cut 2 tubes of biscuits into quarters. Put in the first mixture and stir.
Put in greased Bundt pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Turn out on buttered pan.

title: gnocchi(italian for potato dumplings)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add flour gradually until ball of dough is easy to handle.
Place on floured board and cut in quarters.
Roll out like long snake, about finger size, and cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Drop in boiling water and cook about 30 minutes until tender.
Use with regular spaghetti sauce, or any gravy, and sprinkle with cheese.

title: german nut pudding
directions: Soak gelatin in water.
In pan add eggs, milk and sugar; bring to boil, then add soaked gelatin and cool.
Whip cream and add to mixture with nut meats and vanilla.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add all other ingredients and stir.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese and mushroom bread
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture evenly over bread halves. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: waldorf with orange zest and slivered almonds
directions: Combine ingredients in a noncorrosive bowl.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: breaded pork chops or chicken
directions: Prepare 3 plates, one with flour, one with egg and milk and one with breadcrumbs.
Salt pork chops, then coat with flour, egg mixture and breadcrumbs.
Prepare frying pan with about 1/4-inch of oil; preheat.
Place pork chops in frying pan.
Fry at 300° (medium) for 10 minutes with cover on.
Take cover off and reduce heat to 200°.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Turn pork chops over and repeat above frying.
Fry until crispy brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown the sausage; drain.
Sprinkle croutons in a 9 x 13 glass dish.
Mix well 2 cups of cheese, eggs, seasonings and 1/2 of the sausage.
Pour over the croutons.
Sprinkle with remaining sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Allow to sit for 10 to 15 minutes after baking.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cool, then take it off the bone.
Cut it up into pieces, mix it with onions, peppers, chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
(I don't add salt to mine.)
Set this aside.
Mix chicken soup, mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce and set this aside.
Dip corn tortillas in hot chicken broth, then put in a layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Then a layer of chicken.
Then a layer of cheese.
Continue the layering until all the mixture is used.
Pour soup mixture over all of this.
You can put a layer of tortillas, then chicken, cheese and soup.
Put more cheese on top and bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes 5 cups.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight jars.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup of hot water.
This makes a good gift idea.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese soften first.
Mix with sugar, milk and Dream Whip on medium until well mixed.
Pour into graham cracker crust (pie size).
Add can of cherry pie filling on top, if desired. Chill for 3 hours.

title: angeled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in halves.
Remove yolks.
In medium bowl, mix egg yolks, mayonnaise, honey mustard, pepper and salt; mix until smooth.
With teaspoon, place mixture in clean dry egg white halves.
Sprinkle tops with paprika.

title: pina colada cake(in memory of ruth wolf)
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Combine Eagle Brand and cream of coconut.
Punch holes in cake, while hot, with round handle of wooden spoon.
Pour Eagle Brand and coconut mixture over cake.
Let cool.

title: peanut butter puffs
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Drop spoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: molasses cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together shortening or oleo with sugar. Add eggs and molasses.
Beat until creamy. Add dry ingredients, starting with flour.
Mix well. Roll into teaspoon size balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. In large saucepan, blend first four ingredients plus 1 teaspoon of salt. Stir in 10 cups of water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add lemon juice and food coloring.

title: yonnie's new york style cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, with mixer, cream together cream cheese, Ricotta cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add butter, flour, cornstarch and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Fold in sour cream. Pour batter into ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake cheesecake in the middle of oven for one hour.
Cheesecake will be a bit soft in the center.
Turn off heat.
