Let cake stand in the warm oven for 2 hours with the door closed.
Then, remove cake from oven and set on rack.
Cool completely in pan.
Chill cheesecake, loosely wrapped for at least 2 hours.
Remove side of spring-form pan and transfer the cheesecake to a cake stand or plate.
Makes one 9-inch cheesecake, about 12 servings.

title: butterscotch mocha
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in a saucepan or double boiler over simmering water.
Set aside to cool.
Slightly cream butter and sugar.
Stir in melted butterscotch chips, coffee liqueur and bourbon.

title: rye party rounds
directions: Mix and spread on party round bread. Broil.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and beans.
Put in cake or pie pan.
Top with jalapenos and cheese.
Garnish with black olives and onions.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat well at medium speed.
Mix dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture. Beat well again.
Add apples and nuts; mix well with spoon.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes and remove cake from pan.

title: crockpot chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken, debone, save broth.
Salt chicken to taste when boiling.
Crumble breads together with onion, eggs, sage and pepper.
Add 6 cups of chicken broth (more if needed), mix well. Add chicken and mix well.
Pour mixture into crockpot, put butter on top.
Cover and cook 6 hours on low or 3 hours on high. Dressing will be moist.

title: simple sheet cake
directions: Pour oil into 9 x 13-inch pan; tilt pan until oil covers bottom.
Combine cake mix, eggs and water in pan.
Stir with fork until blended (about 2 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Use knife to loosen sides of cake before serving from pan.
(Don't use if cake is to be taken out of the pan and frosted.)

title: dirty rice
directions: With about 2 cups of water, mix all meats together in a heavy pot on a medium-hot burner.
Add all the seasoning ingredients, except mushroom soup, at the start of cooking.
Cook at medium speed approximately 4 hours.
Stir often.
Then add the cream of mushroom soup.
Continue cooking for 30 minutes.

title: carolina cornbread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Beat egg into the milk and stir in the dry ingredients just enough to blend all the ingredients.
Bake at 400° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan until done (approximately 40 to 45 minutes).

title: maryland lady crab cakes
directions: Remove all cartilage from the crabmeat.
In a bowl, mix breadcrumbs, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crabmeat and mix gently but thoroughly.
Shape into 6 cakes.
Fry in hot fat until brown on both sides.
Makes 6 crab cakes.

title: canadian meat pie(holiday treat)
directions: Combine ground pork, onion and water to cover and cook slowly for about 1 hour.
Refrigerate overnight and remove fat when chilled.
Add spices, salt and pepper and stir in the mashed potatoes.
This makes a filling for 1 double crust pie.
Make vents in top crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed (10 minutes or less).	Cook spinach in microwave safe bowl 7 1/2 minutes total (3 to 3 1/2 minutes; half way turn) and let cool slightly after draining fully the juice.	Once slightly cooled, combine the Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses to the cooked spinach.
To the can of tomato paste add enough water to be a little more than spreadable.
Then add spices to the sauce.
From here the noodles are ready for layering in an 8 x 11 x 2 (IDEAL) pan.
Noodles (4 to 5 per layer), sauce (3/4 of it) spread all over noodles, 4 to 5 noodles then all of cheese mixture spread over noodles.

Top layer of noodles (4 to 5), rest of sauce then sprinkle Parmesan cheese all over sauce. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes uncovered (the last 15 minutes one may cover to prevent more crunchiness in noodles).
Enjoy!

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Reserve broth.
While chicken is cooling, boil spaghetti in chicken broth (for extra flavor).
When spaghetti is done, add tomatoes (and juice), peas, cheese (save 1/4) and chicken, torn into pieces.
Pour into casserole dish; slice remaining cheese on top and bake at 325° until cheese is melted.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef in skillet until brown over medium heat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup mix and chili powder and water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: pecan squares
directions: Melt margarine and sugar in a saucepan over low heat.
Cool. Combine eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts in another bowl.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Divide between two 9-inch square pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk until very thick.
Fold in sour cream and all but 1 cup Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, banana and pudding mixture. Spread remaining pudding and Cool Whip on top. Store in refrigerator.

title: frozen cake
directions: Cream cheese and sugar together.
Combine all fruit.
Mix. Add Cool Whip.
Put ingredients in pan. Freeze. Take out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: amaretto punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in a covered container.
Serve at a slushy consistency.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Put vanilla in first hole, vinegar in second hole and oil in third hole.
Pour water over whole mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: j. france's chicken
directions: Mix ingredients.
Line casserole with 1/2 mixture.
Add chicken breasts.
Pour remainder of mixture over chicken breasts.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover while baking.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Heat peaches.
Put margarine in a baking dish and melt.
Pour mixture over margarine and put hot peaches on top, spreading and pushing down some.
Place in 350° oven until top is a golden brown.
You can use other fruits.

title: tomato relish(good with vegetables and pork)
directions: Cook all ingredients down until you have about 1/2 of what you start with, about 4 to 5 hours.
While still hot, put into pint jars (hot) and seal with hot lids and rings.
Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: meat dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put ground beef and cheese in crock-pot.
Add jalapeno relish and cook until cheese is melted.

title: potatoes salad
directions: Cream potatoes; add Miracle Whip, milk, butter, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir good; add rest of ingredients.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in deep dish pie crust.
Top with butter and top with pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: crab-shrimp dip
directions: Trim and cube (with electric knife) one small loaf white bread. Add eggs, chopped.
Add small chopped onion and cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, add crab meat, shrimp and chopped celery.
Add and mix mayonnaise.
Makes a lot.

title: tex-mex cornbread
directions: Stir all of the ingredients together until well blended, including the melted margarine.
Pour half of the mixture into the 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with a layer of Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: After having prepared beets for canning, mix water, sugar, vinegar and salt together.
Bring to a boil.
Put your beets in and boil for 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal at once.

title: sweet and spicy meatballs
directions: Blend meat with eggs, applesauce and bread crumbs.
Form into 1-inch balls and place in baking dish.
Combine taco sauce, jam and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Chill overnight in refrigerator and skim any fat the next day.
Reheat for serving, about 1/2 hour, at 325°.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together.
Stir in oil, egg, milk and parsley.
Drop by tablespoonful onto boiling chicken or turkey soup.
Reduce heat and cook slowly 10 minutes, uncovered, and 10 minutes, covered.

title: custard cream pudding(or filling)
directions: Gradually add milk to mixture of sugar, cornstarch and salt. Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add about 1/2 cup hot mixture to eggs and blend; carefully combine both mixtures and cook about 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: fudge frosting
directions: In a 2 or 3-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients, except vanilla.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring.
A rolling boil is one that cannot be stirred down. Boil for 1 minute. Cool.
Add vanilla.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator until ready.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil sweet potatoes and drain.
Beat with mixer.
Add 1/2 stick butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Beat again.
Put in buttered dish. Sprinkle over top with 1/2 box yellow cake mix, 1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour over 1 stick melted butter.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 325° to 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until a little crisp.
Pour off juice and put in a baking dish.
Heat milk and soup; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over that, then take the Bisquick and butter and crumb it like you do when putting crumbs on a pie.
Put that on top of cheese and add more cheese on top of that.
Bake about 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Do not prick pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 7 minutes.
In skillet, cook sausage; drain well.
Sprinkle sausage in pie crust and top with cheeses.
Combine beaten eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over all.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Let stand before serving.

title: coconut icing
directions: Combine all ingredients, including beaten egg whites in a heavy 2-quart boiler.
Cook over medium heat; heat to a boil. Boil 3 minutes.
Stir while cooking.
No testing required.
Frost layers.
No way you can be a failure.

title: short-cut stroganoff
directions: Dredge beef in seasoned flour and brown in oil.
Mix soup, wine, onion and mushrooms in a casserole.
Add browned beef. Cover with a tight fitting lid and bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: brown bread
directions: Place oatmeal, molasses, salt and melted shortening in bowl. Pour over this the boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast in warm water with sugar.
Add 6 cups flour or more if needed. Bake 40 minutes using 400° first 15 minutes and 375° for remaining time.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add potatoes and 1 cup water. Cover and simmer until almost cooked.
Add fish and cream or milk. Cover and simmer.
Do not boil.
Salt to taste.
Thicken lightly with mixture of flour, 1/2 teaspoon sugar and water.

title: sweet salties
directions: Melt chocolate
and
shortening
in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add pretzels and peanuts; mix well.
Spread into a buttered 15
x
x 1-inch baking pan.
Chill 20 minutes or until
firm; break
into pieces. Store in airtight container. Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: cheerio nut raisin snack
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Over medium heat, mix brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Stir in baking soda until foamy. Place Cheerios, peanuts and raisins in 4-quart bowl.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until pieces are pea size.
Add 1 tablespoon of water at a time while tossing with fork.
Repeat until fully moistened.
Flatten on floured board and cut to shape or can be pressed in pan evenly to bake.
May use pastry roller to shape rim of crust if desired.

title: pork chops
directions: Spread mustard on one side of chops; garlic powder, salt and pepper on other.
Flour on each side and brown.
Lay flat in shallow pan and cover with soup.
Bake at 350° or cook in slow cooker.

title: poppy seed sandwiches
directions: Combine butter, mustard, worcestershire sauce, onion and poppy seed. Split rolls in half. Cover both sides with butter spread. Top with ham and cheese. Bake sandwiches at 250° for 20 minutes or if frozen at 250° for 30 minutes. Can be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: layered casserole
directions: Press raw hamburger in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt and pepper.
Slice onion and put 1 layer on meat.
Peel and slice enough potatoes to make layer (thickness depends on individual taste), salt and pepper.
Put layer of sliced carrots.
Top with corn.
Pour tomato juice over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet, melt butter over medium heat; saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk; add cheese, green pepper, pimento, pepper and 1/2 cup crumbs.
Pour into a shallow baking dish; top with the remaining 1/2 cup crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: holiday peppermint bark
directions: Line baking sheet with waxed paper. Melt chips in a double boiler stirring until smooth. Place peppermint candy in a heavy duty plastic bag. Crush candies using a rolling pin. While holding strainer over melted chips, pour crushed candy into strainer. Shake to release all small candy pieces; reserve larger candy. Stir the mixture until smooth. Spread mixture to desired thickness on prepared pan. Sprinkle with reserved candy and press lightly. Let stand for about 1 hour or until firm. Break into pieces. Store in an airtight container at room temperature.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add broccoli and mushroom soup.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and melt well.
Add cooked rice and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk on directions to make 2 boxes.
Set aside in bowl.
Make an even layer of graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread about 1/3 of pudding over crackers. Layer graham crackers and pudding ending with layer of crackers. Microwave the frosting so it will pour over layers.
Refrigerate before eating.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat. Add onion and butter.
Cook onion. Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes. Add soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream. Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve with cooked noodles. Good the next day, too.

title: quick chicken lunch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Place sliced onions on top.
Bake in a hot oven until heated through.
Place biscuits on top of mixture and bake until browned.
Delicious and quick!

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and spices.
Add oil and vanilla; mix, adding eggs.
Next, add pineapple, potatoes and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix egg with orange juice and zest.
Blend in melted butter.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid mixture all at once.
Stir until blended.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Grease loaf pan and line with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk white cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, and soda.
Add slowly with milk.
Then fold in egg white. Bake in layer pans until done.
325 degrees.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, sugar and oil together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add carrots, mix well.
Bake in three 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tim's moist toll house cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar, pudding, egg and flavoring.
Slowly add flour.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake at 325° until brown and set.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake 1 large loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or 2 small loaf pans at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: galliano
directions: Boil and cool first three ingredients. Then add next 5 ingredients in large glass container.

title: lemon-jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together;
beat until smooth.
Bake in a 9 1/2 x 11-inch dish at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Stick with toothpick for doneness.
Stick cake with knife while hot all over. Pour glaze over cake while hot.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream shortening, gradually adding sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Alternately add flour (in which baking powder has been sifted) and milk.
Add flavoring.
Add beaten egg whites last. Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quickie date bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar; add egg. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread dough in a greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
When cool, cut into bars.
Can sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in soup, onion, catsup and garlic salt.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat. Do not let boil.
Cook noodles.
Drain.
Toss with butter.
Serve stroganoff over noodles!

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Dust with flour.
In bottom of pan, spread a cup of coconut and a cup of chopped pecans.
Pour cake batter over that.
Mix the oleo with cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and yolks.
Add water and beat together.
Add carrots.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into two well-greased 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: church window candy roll
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in double boiler.
Add the chocolate chips; stir until melted.
Add the chopped nuts; cool.
Add the miniature colored marshmallows; mix.
Take out of pan; form into a roll on a large sheet of tinfoil that has a cup of flake coconut on it. Roll in tinfoil; chill overnight.
Slice.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, sausage, onion, spaghetti sauce and corn flakes.
Roll into ball.
Fry in skillet until brown.
Transfer meat balls to crock-pot.
Put juice into skillet and vinegar with brown sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to boil and let thicken.
Pour the sauce over the meat balls and pineapple chunks.
Cook 2 hours. Ready to serve.

title: aunt marian's goulash
directions: Brown meat, pour off grease.
Add diced onion and cook on low. Add tomatoes.
Cook on low 10 to 15 minutes, then add 28 ounces water and bring to boil.
Add noodles and cook until thick.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and beat 1 minute. Fold in nuts with spoon.
Rub cookie sheet very lightly with butter.
Drop cookies from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° about 20 minutes or until done.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Use measuring cup.
Fill between 1/2 and 2/3 cup with Crisco; fill remaining with milk.
Mix up and cut dough in half.
Makes 2 open-faced or 1 pie (top and bottom).

title: mimi's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup water. Add milk, remaining water, salt, sugar and oil. Stir in flour. Let mixture rise, until doubled about 1 hour, in greased bowl. Punch down and allow to rise for 1 more hour. Punch dough down and form into rolls. Let rolls rise until doubled. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover.
Chill.
Makes 8 cups or 8 servings.

title: pink arctic freeze
directions: Cream together first three ingredients.
Add nuts and cranberry sauce; mix well.
Whip the whipping cream until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour into loaf pan or mold and freeze.
Serve sliced.
Keep frozen.
Serve with turkey, chicken or ham.

title: mint julep
directions: Squeeze lemons and put all ingredients in pan and bring to a boil.
Do not boil.
Remove immediately from burner and steep overnight, if possible.
When cool, strain and refrigerate.
As drink, add 3/4 cup ginger ale to 1/4 cup mixture.

title: pizza spins
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add cheese; melt.
Add ketchup, dash of Worcestershire sauce, dash of oregano and dash of garlic salt. Mix and spread over 2 loaves sliced party rye bread.
Bake at 375° until hot.

title: easy crab casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in a buttered casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pour over apples; top with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix juice from strawberries with enough water to make 1 cup. Mix cake ingredients with juice, jello, eggs and oil.
Bake cake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Makes 3 layers.)

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Add finely chopped onion and margarine together.
Put in microwave.
Heat until margarine melts.
Stir in cornbread mix. Add sour cream, cheese, broccoli and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour into a loaf pan.
Bake at 400° until done.
A must for everyone. Enjoy.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 1/2 cup mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: apples or peaches
directions: Cook until thick, stirring often. Can and seal jars.
Apples or peaches prepared this way can be used for fried pies, casserole cakes and pies.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, using only half of the Wesson oil in the batter.
The other half use in an iron skillet.
Pour into skillet and bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: saucy chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken breast in diagonal strips.
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add chicken strips and brown on all sides.
Remove chicken from skillet, reserving drippings.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Saute until crisp-tender.
Return chicken to skillet.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and cook macaroni.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350°F for 45 min.

title: judy's chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
Add egg yolks, gradually add milk and cook over low heat until mixture is thick. Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.
Add meringue to top and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: great meringue topping
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until frothy. Gradually beat in sugar, a little at a time. Beat until sugar is dissolved and mix is stiff and glassy. Beat in flavoring. Pile meringue onto hot pie filling. Seal the meringue to edges of crust to help prevent shrinking and weeping. Swirl meringue to make decorative top. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool gradually.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar and marshmallows together; refrigerate overnight. The next day, add the remaining ingredients. Mix all together. Chill in refrigerator before serving. Makes 12 servings.

title: mrs. hehman's cookies
directions: Mix together brown sugar, granulated sugar, shortening, vanilla and egg.
Mix separately flour, soda, salt and cinnamon, then add to first mixture.
Add oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoon onto baking sheet.
You can press with glass.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tutti-frutti punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in container of blender; process until smooth. Combine strawberry mixture and water in a large pitcher; cover and chill atleast 3 hours. To serve, add seltzer to juice mixture and stir gently. Serve punch immediately.

title: spicy sausage delight
directions: Cook and crumble sausage. Mix with salsa and cream cheese. Place in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° until bubbly, for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry snow
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Break up angel food cake in lasagna pan.
Spread part of mixture on cakes, then spread blueberries, then mixture again.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold.
Very good!

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the meat and onions, add bell peppers, celery and mushrooms. Add water and simmer for 1 hour.
Season to taste.

title: strawberry pizza pie
directions: Press cookie dough out on a pizza pan.
Bake as directed or until browned.
Cool.
Cream sugar, vanilla and cheese together until smooth.
Spread on cookie.
Mix pie filling and strawberries together.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: surprise jelly
directions: Mix tomatoes and sugar.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Stir in jello. Pour in jars and seal.
Try green tomatoes and raspberry jello.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Combine ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on high for 4 hours.
Serve with Doritos and cheese.
Freezes well.

title: mosiac bean soup recipehouston, texas
directions: Separate beans and spice mix.
Wash beans and place in a large pot.
Cover with water and soak overnight.

title: old fashion cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In bowl, combine cheese, sugar, lemon juice and salt. Mix until well blended; add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Place crust on baking sheet; pour in filling. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: obst boden
directions: Blend these ingredients together thoroughly and spread on a cookie sheet.
Top with fresh sliced fruit or Topping and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Sugar immediately when done.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until soft.
Add hamburger and sausage; cook until brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, water, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer, stirring several times, for 25 minutes.
Cook noodles; set aside.
Mix Ricotta cheese and eggs in bowl.
Place half of noodles in pan; top with 1/3 of meat sauce, 1/2 Ricotta mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Spoon remaining meat sauce on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in medium-size saucepan.
Add onion and sugar; cook and stir 5 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Add bouillon, water and Worcestershire sauce; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: breakfast bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy with electric mixer.
At medium speed, beat in egg, salt, cinnamon and bananas.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn batter into pan. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Cool before cutting.

title: dad's apricot chicken
directions: Remove skin and trim fat from chicken.
Dredge chicken in flour and paprika mixture.
Heat oil in skillet and brown chicken over medium heat.
Drain on paper towels.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese in microwave. Add green chiles and corn. Bake at 350 for about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza(cold)
directions: Fit the 2 packages of crescent rolls in a 10 x 15-inch pan. Stretch dough to fit pan.
(I have cut dough to fit round pan.) Prick with fork.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool. Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing and spread on cooled crust.
Chop assorted vegetables very finely.
Spread (sprinkle) over dough to thickness desired.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over all.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, onions and egg.
Gradually beat in milk or water.
Drop from a spoon into hot fat where fish was fried.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Spread with butter and serve hot with fish.
Makes about 16 small hush puppies.

title: italian soup
directions: Microwave first 4 ingredients.
Make roux with flour and oil. Cook pasta separately.
Combine remaining ingredients. Add carrots last.
Cook till tender.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces, salted and peppered. Place into large stew pot over outdoor fire.
Simmer 4 weeks or until tender.
Serves 3,800 people.
If more people come than you expected, add the rabbits.
But don't do this unless it is really necessary because most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: After draining excess liquid from the pork and beans, combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until boiling; reduce heat to allow mixture to thicken.

title: passover rolls
directions: Boil last 4 ingredients.
Completely remove from heat. Thoroughly mix in matzoh meal.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix, mix, mix.

title: smothered sherry chicken
directions: Brown chicken; arrange pieces in a 9 x 13 pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Remove cover and bake for 15 minutes more or until chicken is tender. Pour sauce over cooked rice and serve with a vegetable.

title: deviled swiss cheese sandwiches
directions: Cream ingredients until blended.
Spread mixture on both sides of 12 slices of bread. Place shaved ham and a slice of Swiss cheese on each of 6 sandwiches.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp dip plate
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of serving plate.
Put cocktail sauce over that.
Rinse shrimp and dry on paper towels.
Put shrimp on top of cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa. Melt butter. Add milk and let come to full boil for 3 to 4 minutes. Take off heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Pour into greased pan. Let cool.

title: kelly's crab dip
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and blend well; pour into baking dish. Top with Monterey Jack cheese and sprinkle lightly with chili powder.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Heat vinegar, salt and water to a boil.
Put dill, grape leaf and garlic in bottom of jar.
Pack cucumbers in clean jars.
Pour boiling liquid over the cucumbers and seal. Allow at least 2 weeks before serving.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Add sliced bananas the next day and serve.

title: christmas candy roll
directions: Cook, sugar, cream and vanilla until it forms a soft ball. Run remaining ingredients through a food processor or blender and then add to sugar mixture.
Stir until stiff, then knead on board sprinkled with powdered sugar until you can mold into a roll. Make 1 or 2 rolls a little more than an inch in diameter.
Wrap in a damp cloth separately and set away to ripen for at least 2 weeks.
Very good!

title: easy lasagna
directions: Combine beef, water, salt and spaghetti sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 of the spaghetti sauce mixture, 1/2 of the cottage cheese and 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat, ending with sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs alternately.
Add dry ingredients with water to sugar and Crisco.
Put batter in cupcake tin and sprinkle chocolate chips on top of batter.
If desired, may also sprinkle nuts on batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Yields 24 cupcakes.

title: french sugar pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, maple sugar and flour.
Spread in crust. Pour cream over pie.
Cover top of pie with crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden.

title: fluffy waffles
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks beaten with milk and melted butter.
Mix together.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Preheat iron and bake.

title: pork chops 'n kraut
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, place drained sauerkraut.
Layer onion and brown sugar on top.
Place chops on top and sprinkle soy sauce over.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Put aluminum foil in pan; fold sides up. Mix together in bowl the cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper. Dip chicken pieces in melted butter, then into crumbs and dry ingredients. Arrange in pan. Spread remaining ingredients on top of chicken. Drizzle in remaining butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: ham loaf for 100
directions: Crush cornflakes slightly.
Combine all ingredients and mold mixture
lightly
into
molds and place in pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brownie cake
directions: Bring to boil the cocoa, oleo, Crisco and water.
Stir in sugar, soda and buttermilk, salt, flour and eggs.
Pour into baking dish; bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
